134  template <unsigned Size, unsigned Max>
135  bool SelectAddrModeIndexedUImm(SDValue N, SDValue &Base, SDValue &OffImm) {
136  // Test if there is an appropriate addressing mode and check if the
137  // immediate fits.
138  bool Found = SelectAddrModeIndexed(N, Size, Base, OffImm);
139  if (Found) {
140  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(OffImm)) {
141  int64_t C = CI->getSExtValue();
142  if (C <= Max)
143  return true;
144  }
145  }
146 
147  // Otherwise, base only, materialize address in register.
148  Base = N;
149  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(N), MVT::i64);
150  return true;
151  }

157  }

165  bool SelectExtractHigh(SDValue N, SDValue &Res) {
166  if (Subtarget->isLittleEndian() && N->getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST)
167  N = N->getOperand(0);
168  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR ||
169  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1)))
170  return false;
171  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
172  EVT LVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
173  unsigned Index = N->getConstantOperandVal(1);
174  if (!VT.is64BitVector() || !LVT.is128BitVector() ||
175  Index != VT.getVectorNumElements())
176  return false;
177  Res = N->getOperand(0);
178  return true;
179  }
180 
181  bool SelectRoundingVLShr(SDValue N, SDValue &Res1, SDValue &Res2) {
182  if (N.getOpcode() != AArch64ISD::VLSHR)
183  return false;
184  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
185  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
186  unsigned ShtAmt = N->getConstantOperandVal(1);
187  if (ShtAmt > VT.getScalarSizeInBits() / 2 || Op.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD)
188  return false;
189 
190  APInt Imm;
191  if (Op.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == AArch64ISD::MOVIshift)
192  Imm = APInt(VT.getScalarSizeInBits(),
193  Op.getOperand(1).getConstantOperandVal(0)
194  << Op.getOperand(1).getConstantOperandVal(1));
195  else if (Op.getOperand(1).getOpcode() == AArch64ISD::DUP &&
196  isa<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1).getOperand(0)))
197  Imm = APInt(VT.getScalarSizeInBits(),
198  Op.getOperand(1).getConstantOperandVal(0));
199  else
200  return false;
201 
202  if (Imm != 1ULL << (ShtAmt - 1))
203  return false;
204 
205  Res1 = Op.getOperand(0);
206  Res2 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShtAmt, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
207  return true;
208  }
209 
210  bool SelectDupZeroOrUndef(SDValue N) {
211  switch(N->getOpcode()) {
212  case ISD::UNDEF:
213  return true;
214  case AArch64ISD::DUP:
215  case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR: {
216  auto Opnd0 = N->getOperand(0);
217  if (isNullConstant(Opnd0))
218  return true;
219  if (isNullFPConstant(Opnd0))
220  return true;
221  break;
222  }
223  default:
224  break;
225  }
226 
227  return false;
228  }
229 
230  bool SelectDupZero(SDValue N) {
231  switch(N->getOpcode()) {
232  case AArch64ISD::DUP:
233  case ISD::SPLAT_VECTOR: {
234  auto Opnd0 = N->getOperand(0);
235  if (isNullConstant(Opnd0))
236  return true;
237  if (isNullFPConstant(Opnd0))
238  return true;
239  break;
240  }
241  }
242 
243  return false;
244  }

271  bool SelectSVEShiftSplatImmR(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) {

281  // Returns a suitable CNT/INC/DEC/RDVL multiplier to calculate VSCALE*N.
282  template<signed Min, signed Max, signed Scale, bool Shift>
283  bool SelectCntImm(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) {
284  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(N))
285  return false;
286 
287  int64_t MulImm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)->getSExtValue();
288  if (Shift)
289  MulImm = 1LL << MulImm;
290 
291  if ((MulImm % std::abs(Scale)) != 0)
292  return false;
293 
294  MulImm /= Scale;
295  if ((MulImm >= Min) && (MulImm <= Max)) {
296  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(MulImm, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
297  return true;
298  }
299 
300  return false;
301  }
302 
303  template <signed Max, signed Scale>
304  bool SelectEXTImm(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) {
305  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(N))
306  return false;
307 
308  int64_t MulImm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)->getSExtValue();
309 
310  if (MulImm >= 0 && MulImm <= Max) {
311  MulImm *= Scale;
312  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(MulImm, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
313  return true;
314  }
315 
316  return false;
317  }

319  template <unsigned BaseReg> bool ImmToTile(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) {
320  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)) {
321  uint64_t C = CI->getZExtValue();
322  Imm = CurDAG->getRegister(BaseReg + C, MVT::Other);
323  return true;
324  }
325  return false;
326  }

328  /// Form sequences of consecutive 64/128-bit registers for use in NEON
329  /// instructions making use of a vector-list (e.g. ldN, tbl). Vecs must have
330  /// between 1 and 4 elements. If it contains a single element that is returned
331  /// unchanged; otherwise a REG_SEQUENCE value is returned.
332  SDValue createDTuple(ArrayRef<SDValue> Vecs);
333  SDValue createQTuple(ArrayRef<SDValue> Vecs);
334  // Form a sequence of SVE registers for instructions using list of vectors,
335  // e.g. structured loads and stores (ldN, stN).
336  SDValue createZTuple(ArrayRef<SDValue> Vecs);
337 
338  // Similar to above, except the register must start at a multiple of the
339  // tuple, e.g. z2 for a 2-tuple, or z8 for a 4-tuple.
340  SDValue createZMulTuple(ArrayRef<SDValue> Regs);

474 INITIALIZE_PASS(AArch64DAGToDAGISel, DEBUG_TYPE, PASS_NAME, false, false)

476 /// isIntImmediate - This method tests to see if the node is a constant
477 /// operand. If so Imm will receive the 32-bit value.
478 static bool isIntImmediate(const SDNode *N, uint64_t &Imm) {
479  if (const ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<const ConstantSDNode>(N)) {
480  Imm = C->getZExtValue();
481  return true;
482  }
483  return false;
484 }
485 
486 // isIntImmediate - This method tests to see if a constant operand.
487 // If so Imm will receive the value.
488 static bool isIntImmediate(SDValue N, uint64_t &Imm) {
489  return isIntImmediate(N.getNode(), Imm);
490 }
491 
492 // isOpcWithIntImmediate - This method tests to see if the node is a specific
493 // opcode and that it has a immediate integer right operand.
494 // If so Imm will receive the 32 bit value.
495 static bool isOpcWithIntImmediate(const SDNode *N, unsigned Opc,
496  uint64_t &Imm) {
497  return N->getOpcode() == Opc &&
498  isIntImmediate(N->getOperand(1).getNode(), Imm);
499 }
500 
501 // isIntImmediateEq - This method tests to see if N is a constant operand that
502 // is equivalent to 'ImmExpected'.
503 #ifndef NDEBUG
504 static bool isIntImmediateEq(SDValue N, const uint64_t ImmExpected) {
505  uint64_t Imm;
506  if (!isIntImmediate(N.getNode(), Imm))
507  return false;
508  return Imm == ImmExpected;
509 }
510 #endif
511 
512 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectInlineAsmMemoryOperand(
513  const SDValue &Op, unsigned ConstraintID, std::vector<SDValue> &OutOps) {
514  switch(ConstraintID) {
515  default:
516  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected asm memory constraint");
517  case InlineAsm::Constraint_m:
518  case InlineAsm::Constraint_o:
519  case InlineAsm::Constraint_Q:
520  // We need to make sure that this one operand does not end up in XZR, thus
521  // require the address to be in a PointerRegClass register.
522  const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo();
523  const TargetRegisterClass *TRC = TRI->getPointerRegClass(*MF);
524  SDLoc dl(Op);
525  SDValue RC = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(TRC->getID(), dl, MVT::i64);
526  SDValue NewOp =
527  SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::COPY_TO_REGCLASS,
528  dl, Op.getValueType(),
529  Op, RC), 0);
530  OutOps.push_back(NewOp);
531  return false;
532  }
533  return true;
534 }
535 
536 /// SelectArithImmed - Select an immediate value that can be represented as
537 /// a 12-bit value shifted left by either 0 or 12. If so, return true with
538 /// Val set to the 12-bit value and Shift set to the shifter operand.
539 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectArithImmed(SDValue N, SDValue &Val,
540  SDValue &Shift) {
541  // This function is called from the addsub_shifted_imm ComplexPattern,
542  // which lists [imm] as the list of opcode it's interested in, however
543  // we still need to check whether the operand is actually an immediate
544  // here because the ComplexPattern opcode list is only used in
545  // root-level opcode matching.
546  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(N.getNode()))
547  return false;
548 
549  uint64_t Immed = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getNode())->getZExtValue();
550  unsigned ShiftAmt;
551 
552  if (Immed >> 12 == 0) {
553  ShiftAmt = 0;
554  } else if ((Immed & 0xfff) == 0 && Immed >> 24 == 0) {
555  ShiftAmt = 12;
556  Immed = Immed >> 12;
557  } else
558  return false;
559 
560  unsigned ShVal = AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSL, ShiftAmt);
561  SDLoc dl(N);
562  Val = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Immed, dl, MVT::i32);
563  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShVal, dl, MVT::i32);
564  return true;
565 }
566 
567 /// SelectNegArithImmed - As above, but negates the value before trying to
568 /// select it.
569 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectNegArithImmed(SDValue N, SDValue &Val,
570  SDValue &Shift) {
571  // This function is called from the addsub_shifted_imm ComplexPattern,
572  // which lists [imm] as the list of opcode it's interested in, however
573  // we still need to check whether the operand is actually an immediate
574  // here because the ComplexPattern opcode list is only used in
575  // root-level opcode matching.
576  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(N.getNode()))
577  return false;
578 
579  // The immediate operand must be a 24-bit zero-extended immediate.
580  uint64_t Immed = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getNode())->getZExtValue();
581 
582  // This negation is almost always valid, but "cmp wN, #0" and "cmn wN, #0"
583  // have the opposite effect on the C flag, so this pattern mustn't match under
584  // those circumstances.
585  if (Immed == 0)
586  return false;
587 
588  if (N.getValueType() == MVT::i32)
589  Immed = ~((uint32_t)Immed) + 1;
590  else
591  Immed = ~Immed + 1ULL;
592  if (Immed & 0xFFFFFFFFFF000000ULL)
593  return false;
594 
595  Immed &= 0xFFFFFFULL;
596  return SelectArithImmed(CurDAG->getConstant(Immed, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32), Val,
597  Shift);
598 }
599 
600 /// getShiftTypeForNode - Translate a shift node to the corresponding
601 /// ShiftType value.
602 static AArch64_AM::ShiftExtendType getShiftTypeForNode(SDValue N) {
603  switch (N.getOpcode()) {
604  default:
605  return AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend;
606  case ISD::SHL:
607  return AArch64_AM::LSL;
608  case ISD::SRL:
609  return AArch64_AM::LSR;
610  case ISD::SRA:
611  return AArch64_AM::ASR;
612  case ISD::ROTR:
613  return AArch64_AM::ROR;
614  }
615 }
616 
617 /// Determine whether it is worth it to fold SHL into the addressing
618 /// mode.
619 static bool isWorthFoldingSHL(SDValue V) {
620  assert(V.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && "invalid opcode");
621  // It is worth folding logical shift of up to three places.
622  auto *CSD = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getOperand(1));
623  if (!CSD)
624  return false;
625  unsigned ShiftVal = CSD->getZExtValue();
626  if (ShiftVal > 3)
627  return false;
628 
629  // Check if this particular node is reused in any non-memory related
630  // operation. If yes, do not try to fold this node into the address
631  // computation, since the computation will be kept.
632  const SDNode *Node = V.getNode();
633  for (SDNode *UI : Node->uses())
634  if (!isa<MemSDNode>(*UI))
635  for (SDNode *UII : UI->uses())
636  if (!isa<MemSDNode>(*UII))
637  return false;
638  return true;
639 }
640 
641 /// Determine whether it is worth to fold V into an extended register.
642 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::isWorthFolding(SDValue V) const {
643  // Trivial if we are optimizing for code size or if there is only
644  // one use of the value.
645  if (CurDAG->shouldOptForSize() || V.hasOneUse())
646  return true;
647  // If a subtarget has a fastpath LSL we can fold a logical shift into
648  // the addressing mode and save a cycle.
649  if (Subtarget->hasLSLFast() && V.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL &&
650  isWorthFoldingSHL(V))
651  return true;
652  if (Subtarget->hasLSLFast() && V.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) {
653  const SDValue LHS = V.getOperand(0);
654  const SDValue RHS = V.getOperand(1);
655  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && isWorthFoldingSHL(LHS))
656  return true;
657  if (RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && isWorthFoldingSHL(RHS))
658  return true;
659  }
660 
661  // It hurts otherwise, since the value will be reused.
662  return false;
663 }
664 
665 /// and (shl/srl/sra, x, c), mask --> shl (srl/sra, x, c1), c2
666 /// to select more shifted register
667 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectShiftedRegisterFromAnd(SDValue N, SDValue &Reg,
668  SDValue &Shift) {
669  EVT VT = N.getValueType();
670  if (VT != MVT::i32 && VT != MVT::i64)
671  return false;
672 
673  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::AND || !N->hasOneUse())
674  return false;
675  SDValue LHS = N.getOperand(0);
676  if (!LHS->hasOneUse())
677  return false;
678 
679  unsigned LHSOpcode = LHS->getOpcode();
680  if (LHSOpcode != ISD::SHL && LHSOpcode != ISD::SRL && LHSOpcode != ISD::SRA)
681  return false;
682 
683  ConstantSDNode *ShiftAmtNode = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(1));
684  if (!ShiftAmtNode)
685  return false;
686 
687  uint64_t ShiftAmtC = ShiftAmtNode->getZExtValue();
688  ConstantSDNode *RHSC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(1));
689  if (!RHSC)
690  return false;
691 
692  APInt AndMask = RHSC->getAPIntValue();
693  unsigned LowZBits, MaskLen;
694  if (!AndMask.isShiftedMask(LowZBits, MaskLen))
695  return false;
696 
697  unsigned BitWidth = N.getValueSizeInBits();
698  SDLoc DL(LHS);
699  uint64_t NewShiftC;
700  unsigned NewShiftOp;
701  if (LHSOpcode == ISD::SHL) {
702  // LowZBits <= ShiftAmtC will fall into isBitfieldPositioningOp
703  // BitWidth != LowZBits + MaskLen doesn't match the pattern
704  if (LowZBits <= ShiftAmtC || (BitWidth != LowZBits + MaskLen))
705  return false;
706 
707  NewShiftC = LowZBits - ShiftAmtC;
708  NewShiftOp = VT == MVT::i64 ? AArch64::UBFMXri : AArch64::UBFMWri;
709  } else {
710  if (LowZBits == 0)
711  return false;
712 
713  // NewShiftC >= BitWidth will fall into isBitfieldExtractOp
714  NewShiftC = LowZBits + ShiftAmtC;
715  if (NewShiftC >= BitWidth)
716  return false;
717 
718  // SRA need all high bits
719  if (LHSOpcode == ISD::SRA && (BitWidth != (LowZBits + MaskLen)))
720  return false;
721 
722  // SRL high bits can be 0 or 1
723  if (LHSOpcode == ISD::SRL && (BitWidth > (NewShiftC + MaskLen)))
724  return false;
725 
726  if (LHSOpcode == ISD::SRL)
727  NewShiftOp = VT == MVT::i64 ? AArch64::UBFMXri : AArch64::UBFMWri;
728  else
729  NewShiftOp = VT == MVT::i64 ? AArch64::SBFMXri : AArch64::SBFMWri;
730  }
731 
732  assert(NewShiftC < BitWidth && "Invalid shift amount");
733  SDValue NewShiftAmt = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(NewShiftC, DL, VT);
734  SDValue BitWidthMinus1 = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(BitWidth - 1, DL, VT);
735  Reg = SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(NewShiftOp, DL, VT, LHS->getOperand(0),
736  NewShiftAmt, BitWidthMinus1),
737  0);
738  unsigned ShVal = AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSL, LowZBits);
739  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShVal, DL, MVT::i32);
740  return true;
741 }
742 
743 /// SelectShiftedRegister - Select a "shifted register" operand. If the value
744 /// is not shifted, set the Shift operand to default of "LSL 0". The logical
745 /// instructions allow the shifted register to be rotated, but the arithmetic
746 /// instructions do not. The AllowROR parameter specifies whether ROR is
747 /// supported.
748 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectShiftedRegister(SDValue N, bool AllowROR,
749  SDValue &Reg, SDValue &Shift) {
750  if (SelectShiftedRegisterFromAnd(N, Reg, Shift))
751  return true;
752 
753  AArch64_AM::ShiftExtendType ShType = getShiftTypeForNode(N);
754  if (ShType == AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend)
755  return false;
756  if (!AllowROR && ShType == AArch64_AM::ROR)
757  return false;
758 
759  if (ConstantSDNode *RHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(1))) {
760  unsigned BitSize = N.getValueSizeInBits();
761  unsigned Val = RHS->getZExtValue() & (BitSize - 1);
762  unsigned ShVal = AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(ShType, Val);
763 
764  Reg = N.getOperand(0);
765  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShVal, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
766  return isWorthFolding(N);
767  }
768 
769  return false;
770 }
771 
772 /// getExtendTypeForNode - Translate an extend node to the corresponding
773 /// ExtendType value.
774 static AArch64_AM::ShiftExtendType
775 getExtendTypeForNode(SDValue N, bool IsLoadStore = false) {
776  if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND ||
777  N.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG) {
778  EVT SrcVT;
779  if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG)
780  SrcVT = cast<VTSDNode>(N.getOperand(1))->getVT();
781  else
782  SrcVT = N.getOperand(0).getValueType();
783 
784  if (!IsLoadStore && SrcVT == MVT::i8)
785  return AArch64_AM::SXTB;
786  else if (!IsLoadStore && SrcVT == MVT::i16)
787  return AArch64_AM::SXTH;
788  else if (SrcVT == MVT::i32)
789  return AArch64_AM::SXTW;
790  assert(SrcVT != MVT::i64 && "extend from 64-bits?");
791 
792  return AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend;
793  } else if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND ||
794  N.getOpcode() == ISD::ANY_EXTEND) {
795  EVT SrcVT = N.getOperand(0).getValueType();
796  if (!IsLoadStore && SrcVT == MVT::i8)
797  return AArch64_AM::UXTB;
798  else if (!IsLoadStore && SrcVT == MVT::i16)
799  return AArch64_AM::UXTH;
800  else if (SrcVT == MVT::i32)
801  return AArch64_AM::UXTW;
802  assert(SrcVT != MVT::i64 && "extend from 64-bits?");
803 
804  return AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend;
805  } else if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::AND) {
806  ConstantSDNode *CSD = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(1));
807  if (!CSD)
808  return AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend;
809  uint64_t AndMask = CSD->getZExtValue();
810 
811  switch (AndMask) {
812  default:
813  return AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend;
814  case 0xFF:
815  return !IsLoadStore ? AArch64_AM::UXTB : AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend;
816  case 0xFFFF:
817  return !IsLoadStore ? AArch64_AM::UXTH : AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend;
818  case 0xFFFFFFFF:
819  return AArch64_AM::UXTW;
820  }
821  }
822 
823  return AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend;
824 }
825 
826 // Helper for SelectMLAV64LaneV128 - Recognize high lane extracts.
827 static bool checkHighLaneIndex(SDNode *DL, SDValue &LaneOp, int &LaneIdx) {
828  if (DL->getOpcode() != AArch64ISD::DUPLANE16 &&
829  DL->getOpcode() != AArch64ISD::DUPLANE32)
830  return false;
831 
832  SDValue SV = DL->getOperand(0);
833  if (SV.getOpcode() != ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR)
834  return false;
835 
836  SDValue EV = SV.getOperand(1);
837  if (EV.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR)
838  return false;
839 
840  ConstantSDNode *DLidx = cast<ConstantSDNode>(DL->getOperand(1).getNode());
841  ConstantSDNode *EVidx = cast<ConstantSDNode>(EV.getOperand(1).getNode());
842  LaneIdx = DLidx->getSExtValue() + EVidx->getSExtValue();
843  LaneOp = EV.getOperand(0);
844 
845  return true;
846 }
847 
848 // Helper for SelectOpcV64LaneV128 - Recognize operations where one operand is a
849 // high lane extract.
850 static bool checkV64LaneV128(SDValue Op0, SDValue Op1, SDValue &StdOp,
851  SDValue &LaneOp, int &LaneIdx) {
852 
853  if (!checkHighLaneIndex(Op0.getNode(), LaneOp, LaneIdx)) {
854  std::swap(Op0, Op1);
855  if (!checkHighLaneIndex(Op0.getNode(), LaneOp, LaneIdx))
856  return false;
857  }
858  StdOp = Op1;
859  return true;
860 }
861 
862 /// SelectMLAV64LaneV128 - AArch64 supports vector MLAs where one multiplicand
863 /// is a lane in the upper half of a 128-bit vector. Recognize and select this
864 /// so that we don't emit unnecessary lane extracts.
865 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryMLAV64LaneV128(SDNode *N) {
866  SDLoc dl(N);
867  SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
868  SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
869  SDValue MLAOp1; // Will hold ordinary multiplicand for MLA.
870  SDValue MLAOp2; // Will hold lane-accessed multiplicand for MLA.
871  int LaneIdx = -1; // Will hold the lane index.
872 
873  if (Op1.getOpcode() != ISD::MUL ||
874  !checkV64LaneV128(Op1.getOperand(0), Op1.getOperand(1), MLAOp1, MLAOp2,
875  LaneIdx)) {
876  std::swap(Op0, Op1);
877  if (Op1.getOpcode() != ISD::MUL ||
878  !checkV64LaneV128(Op1.getOperand(0), Op1.getOperand(1), MLAOp1, MLAOp2,
879  LaneIdx))
880  return false;
881  }
882 
883  SDValue LaneIdxVal = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LaneIdx, dl, MVT::i64);
884 
885  SDValue Ops[] = { Op0, MLAOp1, MLAOp2, LaneIdxVal };
886 
887  unsigned MLAOpc = ~0U;
888 
889  switch (N->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) {
890  default:
891  llvm_unreachable("Unrecognized MLA.");
892  case MVT::v4i16:
893  MLAOpc = AArch64::MLAv4i16_indexed;
894  break;
895  case MVT::v8i16:
896  MLAOpc = AArch64::MLAv8i16_indexed;
897  break;
898  case MVT::v2i32:
899  MLAOpc = AArch64::MLAv2i32_indexed;
900  break;
901  case MVT::v4i32:
902  MLAOpc = AArch64::MLAv4i32_indexed;
903  break;
904  }
905 
906  ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(MLAOpc, dl, N->getValueType(0), Ops));
907  return true;
908 }
909 
910 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryMULLV64LaneV128(unsigned IntNo, SDNode *N) {
911  SDLoc dl(N);
912  SDValue SMULLOp0;
913  SDValue SMULLOp1;
914  int LaneIdx;
915 
916  if (!checkV64LaneV128(N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2), SMULLOp0, SMULLOp1,
917  LaneIdx))
918  return false;
919 
920  SDValue LaneIdxVal = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LaneIdx, dl, MVT::i64);
921 
922  SDValue Ops[] = { SMULLOp0, SMULLOp1, LaneIdxVal };
923 
924  unsigned SMULLOpc = ~0U;
925 
926  if (IntNo == Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_smull) {
927  switch (N->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) {
928  default:
929  llvm_unreachable("Unrecognized SMULL.");
930  case MVT::v4i32:
931  SMULLOpc = AArch64::SMULLv4i16_indexed;
932  break;
933  case MVT::v2i64:
934  SMULLOpc = AArch64::SMULLv2i32_indexed;
935  break;
936  }
937  } else if (IntNo == Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_umull) {
938  switch (N->getSimpleValueType(0).SimpleTy) {
939  default:
940  llvm_unreachable("Unrecognized SMULL.");
941  case MVT::v4i32:
942  SMULLOpc = AArch64::UMULLv4i16_indexed;
943  break;
944  case MVT::v2i64:
945  SMULLOpc = AArch64::UMULLv2i32_indexed;
946  break;
947  }
948  } else
949  llvm_unreachable("Unrecognized intrinsic.");
950 
951  ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(SMULLOpc, dl, N->getValueType(0), Ops));
952  return true;
953 }
954 
955 /// Instructions that accept extend modifiers like UXTW expect the register
956 /// being extended to be a GPR32, but the incoming DAG might be acting on a
957 /// GPR64 (either via SEXT_INREG or AND). Extract the appropriate low bits if
958 /// this is the case.
959 static SDValue narrowIfNeeded(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDValue N) {
960  if (N.getValueType() == MVT::i32)
961  return N;
962 
963  SDLoc dl(N);
964  SDValue SubReg = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::sub_32, dl, MVT::i32);
965  MachineSDNode *Node = CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG,
966  dl, MVT::i32, N, SubReg);
967  return SDValue(Node, 0);
968 }
969 
970 // Returns a suitable CNT/INC/DEC/RDVL multiplier to calculate VSCALE*N.
971 template<signed Low, signed High, signed Scale>
972 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectRDVLImm(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) {
973  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(N))
974  return false;
975 
976  int64_t MulImm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)->getSExtValue();
977  if ((MulImm % std::abs(Scale)) == 0) {
978  int64_t RDVLImm = MulImm / Scale;
979  if ((RDVLImm >= Low) && (RDVLImm <= High)) {
980  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RDVLImm, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
981  return true;
982  }
983  }
984 
985  return false;
986 }
987 
988 /// SelectArithExtendedRegister - Select a "extended register" operand. This
989 /// operand folds in an extend followed by an optional left shift.
990 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectArithExtendedRegister(SDValue N, SDValue &Reg,
991  SDValue &Shift) {
992  unsigned ShiftVal = 0;
993  AArch64_AM::ShiftExtendType Ext;
994 
995  if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
996  ConstantSDNode *CSD = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(1));
997  if (!CSD)
998  return false;
999  ShiftVal = CSD->getZExtValue();
1000  if (ShiftVal > 4)
1001  return false;
1002 
1003  Ext = getExtendTypeForNode(N.getOperand(0));
1004  if (Ext == AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend)
1005  return false;
1006 
1007  Reg = N.getOperand(0).getOperand(0);
1008  } else {
1009  Ext = getExtendTypeForNode(N);
1010  if (Ext == AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend)
1011  return false;
1012 
1013  Reg = N.getOperand(0);
1014 
1015  // Don't match if free 32-bit -> 64-bit zext can be used instead. Use the
1016  // isDef32 as a heuristic for when the operand is likely to be a 32bit def.
1017  auto isDef32 = [](SDValue N) {
1018  unsigned Opc = N.getOpcode();
1019  return Opc != ISD::TRUNCATE && Opc != TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG &&
1020  Opc != ISD::CopyFromReg && Opc != ISD::AssertSext &&
1021  Opc != ISD::AssertZext && Opc != ISD::AssertAlign &&
1022  Opc != ISD::FREEZE;
1023  };
1024  if (Ext == AArch64_AM::UXTW && Reg->getValueType(0).getSizeInBits() == 32 &&
1025  isDef32(Reg))
1026  return false;
1027  }
1028 
1029  // AArch64 mandates that the RHS of the operation must use the smallest
1030  // register class that could contain the size being extended from. Thus,
1031  // if we're folding a (sext i8), we need the RHS to be a GPR32, even though
1032  // there might not be an actual 32-bit value in the program. We can
1033  // (harmlessly) synthesize one by injected an EXTRACT_SUBREG here.
1034  assert(Ext != AArch64_AM::UXTX && Ext != AArch64_AM::SXTX);
1035  Reg = narrowIfNeeded(CurDAG, Reg);
1036  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(getArithExtendImm(Ext, ShiftVal), SDLoc(N),
1037  MVT::i32);
1038  return isWorthFolding(N);
1039 }
1040 
1041 /// SelectArithUXTXRegister - Select a "UXTX register" operand. This
1042 /// operand is refered by the instructions have SP operand
1043 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectArithUXTXRegister(SDValue N, SDValue &Reg,
1044  SDValue &Shift) {
1045  unsigned ShiftVal = 0;
1046  AArch64_AM::ShiftExtendType Ext;
1047 
1048  if (N.getOpcode() != ISD::SHL)
1049  return false;
1050 
1051  ConstantSDNode *CSD = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(1));
1052  if (!CSD)
1053  return false;
1054  ShiftVal = CSD->getZExtValue();
1055  if (ShiftVal > 4)
1056  return false;
1057 
1058  Ext = AArch64_AM::UXTX;
1059  Reg = N.getOperand(0);
1060  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(getArithExtendImm(Ext, ShiftVal), SDLoc(N),
1061  MVT::i32);
1062  return isWorthFolding(N);
1063 }
1064 
1065 /// If there's a use of this ADDlow that's not itself a load/store then we'll
1066 /// need to create a real ADD instruction from it anyway and there's no point in
1067 /// folding it into the mem op. Theoretically, it shouldn't matter, but there's
1068 /// a single pseudo-instruction for an ADRP/ADD pair so over-aggressive folding
1069 /// leads to duplicated ADRP instructions.
1070 static bool isWorthFoldingADDlow(SDValue N) {
1071  for (auto *Use : N->uses()) {
1072  if (Use->getOpcode() != ISD::LOAD && Use->getOpcode() != ISD::STORE &&
1073  Use->getOpcode() != ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD &&
1074  Use->getOpcode() != ISD::ATOMIC_STORE)
1075  return false;
1076 
1077  // ldar and stlr have much more restrictive addressing modes (just a
1078  // register).
1079  if (isStrongerThanMonotonic(cast<MemSDNode>(Use)->getSuccessOrdering()))
1080  return false;
1081  }
1082 
1083  return true;
1084 }
1085 
1086 /// SelectAddrModeIndexedBitWidth - Select a "register plus scaled (un)signed BW-bit
1087 /// immediate" address. The "Size" argument is the size in bytes of the memory
1088 /// reference, which determines the scale.
1089 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrModeIndexedBitWidth(SDValue N, bool IsSignedImm,
1090  unsigned BW, unsigned Size,
1091  SDValue &Base,
1092  SDValue &OffImm) {
1093  SDLoc dl(N);
1094  const DataLayout &DL = CurDAG->getDataLayout();
1095  const TargetLowering *TLI = getTargetLowering();
1096  if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) {
1097  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(N)->getIndex();
1098  Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI, TLI->getPointerTy(DL));
1099  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, dl, MVT::i64);
1100  return true;
1101  }
1102 
1103  // As opposed to the (12-bit) Indexed addressing mode below, the 7/9-bit signed
1104  // selected here doesn't support labels/immediates, only base+offset.
1105  if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(N)) {
1106  if (ConstantSDNode *RHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(1))) {
1107  if (IsSignedImm) {
1108  int64_t RHSC = RHS->getSExtValue();
1109  unsigned Scale = Log2_32(Size);
1110  int64_t Range = 0x1LL << (BW - 1);
1111 
1112  if ((RHSC & (Size - 1)) == 0 && RHSC >= -(Range << Scale) &&
1113  RHSC < (Range << Scale)) {
1114  Base = N.getOperand(0);
1115  if (Base.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) {
1116  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Base)->getIndex();
1117  Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI, TLI->getPointerTy(DL));
1118  }
1119  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RHSC >> Scale, dl, MVT::i64);
1120  return true;
1121  }
1122  } else {
1123  // unsigned Immediate
1124  uint64_t RHSC = RHS->getZExtValue();
1125  unsigned Scale = Log2_32(Size);
1126  uint64_t Range = 0x1ULL << BW;
1127 
1128  if ((RHSC & (Size - 1)) == 0 && RHSC < (Range << Scale)) {
1129  Base = N.getOperand(0);
1130  if (Base.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) {
1131  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Base)->getIndex();
1132  Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI, TLI->getPointerTy(DL));
1133  }
1134  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RHSC >> Scale, dl, MVT::i64);
1135  return true;
1136  }
1137  }
1138  }
1139  }
1140  // Base only. The address will be materialized into a register before
1141  // the memory is accessed.
1142  // add x0, Xbase, #offset
1143  // stp x1, x2, [x0]
1144  Base = N;
1145  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, dl, MVT::i64);
1146  return true;
1147 }
1148 
1149 /// SelectAddrModeIndexed - Select a "register plus scaled unsigned 12-bit
1150 /// immediate" address. The "Size" argument is the size in bytes of the memory
1151 /// reference, which determines the scale.
1152 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrModeIndexed(SDValue N, unsigned Size,
1153  SDValue &Base, SDValue &OffImm) {
1154  SDLoc dl(N);
1155  const DataLayout &DL = CurDAG->getDataLayout();
1156  const TargetLowering *TLI = getTargetLowering();
1157  if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) {
1158  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(N)->getIndex();
1159  Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI, TLI->getPointerTy(DL));
1160  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, dl, MVT::i64);
1161  return true;
1162  }
1163 
1164  if (N.getOpcode() == AArch64ISD::ADDlow && isWorthFoldingADDlow(N)) {
1165  GlobalAddressSDNode *GAN =
1166  dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(N.getOperand(1).getNode());
1167  Base = N.getOperand(0);
1168  OffImm = N.getOperand(1);
1169  if (!GAN)
1170  return true;
1171 
1172  if (GAN->getOffset() % Size == 0 &&
1173  GAN->getGlobal()->getPointerAlignment(DL) >= Size)
1174  return true;
1175  }
1176 
1177  if (CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(N)) {
1178  if (ConstantSDNode *RHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(1))) {
1179  int64_t RHSC = (int64_t)RHS->getZExtValue();
1180  unsigned Scale = Log2_32(Size);
1181  if ((RHSC & (Size - 1)) == 0 && RHSC >= 0 && RHSC < (0x1000 << Scale)) {
1182  Base = N.getOperand(0);
1183  if (Base.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) {
1184  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Base)->getIndex();
1185  Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI, TLI->getPointerTy(DL));
1186  }
1187  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RHSC >> Scale, dl, MVT::i64);
1188  return true;
1189  }
1190  }
1191  }
1192 
1193  // Before falling back to our general case, check if the unscaled
1194  // instructions can handle this. If so, that's preferable.
1195  if (SelectAddrModeUnscaled(N, Size, Base, OffImm))
1196  return false;
1197 
1198  // Base only. The address will be materialized into a register before
1199  // the memory is accessed.
1200  // add x0, Xbase, #offset
1201  // ldr x0, [x0]
1202  Base = N;
1203  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, dl, MVT::i64);
1204  return true;
1205 }
1206 
1207 /// SelectAddrModeUnscaled - Select a "register plus unscaled signed 9-bit
1208 /// immediate" address. This should only match when there is an offset that
1209 /// is not valid for a scaled immediate addressing mode. The "Size" argument
1210 /// is the size in bytes of the memory reference, which is needed here to know
1211 /// what is valid for a scaled immediate.
1212 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrModeUnscaled(SDValue N, unsigned Size,
1213  SDValue &Base,
1214  SDValue &OffImm) {
1215  if (!CurDAG->isBaseWithConstantOffset(N))
1216  return false;
1217  if (ConstantSDNode *RHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(1))) {
1218  int64_t RHSC = RHS->getSExtValue();
1219  // If the offset is valid as a scaled immediate, don't match here.
1220  if ((RHSC & (Size - 1)) == 0 && RHSC >= 0 &&
1221  RHSC < (0x1000 << Log2_32(Size)))
1222  return false;
1223  if (RHSC >= -256 && RHSC < 256) {
1224  Base = N.getOperand(0);
1225  if (Base.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) {
1226  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Base)->getIndex();
1227  const TargetLowering *TLI = getTargetLowering();
1228  Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(
1229  FI, TLI->getPointerTy(CurDAG->getDataLayout()));
1230  }
1231  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RHSC, SDLoc(N), MVT::i64);
1232  return true;
1233  }
1234  }
1235  return false;
1236 }
1237 
1238 static SDValue Widen(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDValue N) {
1239  SDLoc dl(N);
1240  SDValue SubReg = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::sub_32, dl, MVT::i32);
1241  SDValue ImpDef = SDValue(
1242  CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF, dl, MVT::i64), 0);
1243  MachineSDNode *Node = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
1244  TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG, dl, MVT::i64, ImpDef, N, SubReg);
1245  return SDValue(Node, 0);
1246 }
1247 
1248 /// Check if the given SHL node (\p N), can be used to form an
1249 /// extended register for an addressing mode.
1250 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectExtendedSHL(SDValue N, unsigned Size,
1251  bool WantExtend, SDValue &Offset,
1252  SDValue &SignExtend) {
1253  assert(N.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL && "Invalid opcode.");
1254  ConstantSDNode *CSD = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N.getOperand(1));
1255  if (!CSD || (CSD->getZExtValue() & 0x7) != CSD->getZExtValue())
1256  return false;
1257 
1258  SDLoc dl(N);
1259  if (WantExtend) {
1260  AArch64_AM::ShiftExtendType Ext =
1261  getExtendTypeForNode(N.getOperand(0), true);
1262  if (Ext == AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend)
1263  return false;
1264 
1265  Offset = narrowIfNeeded(CurDAG, N.getOperand(0).getOperand(0));
1266  SignExtend = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Ext == AArch64_AM::SXTW, dl,
1267  MVT::i32);
1268  } else {
1269  Offset = N.getOperand(0);
1270  SignExtend = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, dl, MVT::i32);
1271  }
1272 
1273  unsigned LegalShiftVal = Log2_32(Size);
1274  unsigned ShiftVal = CSD->getZExtValue();
1275 
1276  if (ShiftVal != 0 && ShiftVal != LegalShiftVal)
1277  return false;
1278 
1279  return isWorthFolding(N);
1280 }
1281 
1282 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrModeWRO(SDValue N, unsigned Size,
1283  SDValue &Base, SDValue &Offset,
1284  SDValue &SignExtend,
1285  SDValue &DoShift) {
1286  if (N.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD)
1287  return false;
1288  SDValue LHS = N.getOperand(0);
1289  SDValue RHS = N.getOperand(1);
1290  SDLoc dl(N);
1291 
1292  // We don't want to match immediate adds here, because they are better lowered
1293  // to the register-immediate addressing modes.
1294  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(LHS) || isa<ConstantSDNode>(RHS))
1295  return false;
1296 
1297  // Check if this particular node is reused in any non-memory related
1298  // operation. If yes, do not try to fold this node into the address
1299  // computation, since the computation will be kept.
1300  const SDNode *Node = N.getNode();
1301  for (SDNode *UI : Node->uses()) {
1302  if (!isa<MemSDNode>(*UI))
1303  return false;
1304  }
1305 
1306  // Remember if it is worth folding N when it produces extended register.
1307  bool IsExtendedRegisterWorthFolding = isWorthFolding(N);
1308 
1309  // Try to match a shifted extend on the RHS.
1310  if (IsExtendedRegisterWorthFolding && RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL &&
1311  SelectExtendedSHL(RHS, Size, true, Offset, SignExtend)) {
1312  Base = LHS;
1313  DoShift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(true, dl, MVT::i32);
1314  return true;
1315  }
1316 
1317  // Try to match a shifted extend on the LHS.
1318  if (IsExtendedRegisterWorthFolding && LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL &&
1319  SelectExtendedSHL(LHS, Size, true, Offset, SignExtend)) {
1320  Base = RHS;
1321  DoShift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(true, dl, MVT::i32);
1322  return true;
1323  }
1324 
1325  // There was no shift, whatever else we find.
1326  DoShift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(false, dl, MVT::i32);
1327 
1328  AArch64_AM::ShiftExtendType Ext = AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend;
1329  // Try to match an unshifted extend on the LHS.
1330  if (IsExtendedRegisterWorthFolding &&
1331  (Ext = getExtendTypeForNode(LHS, true)) !=
1332  AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend) {
1333  Base = RHS;
1334  Offset = narrowIfNeeded(CurDAG, LHS.getOperand(0));
1335  SignExtend = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Ext == AArch64_AM::SXTW, dl,
1336  MVT::i32);
1337  if (isWorthFolding(LHS))
1338  return true;
1339  }
1340 
1341  // Try to match an unshifted extend on the RHS.
1342  if (IsExtendedRegisterWorthFolding &&
1343  (Ext = getExtendTypeForNode(RHS, true)) !=
1344  AArch64_AM::InvalidShiftExtend) {
1345  Base = LHS;
1346  Offset = narrowIfNeeded(CurDAG, RHS.getOperand(0));
1347  SignExtend = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Ext == AArch64_AM::SXTW, dl,
1348  MVT::i32);
1349  if (isWorthFolding(RHS))
1350  return true;
1351  }
1352 
1353  return false;
1354 }
1355 
1356 // Check if the given immediate is preferred by ADD. If an immediate can be
1357 // encoded in an ADD, or it can be encoded in an "ADD LSL #12" and can not be
1358 // encoded by one MOVZ, return true.
1359 static bool isPreferredADD(int64_t ImmOff) {
1360  // Constant in [0x0, 0xfff] can be encoded in ADD.
1361  if ((ImmOff & 0xfffffffffffff000LL) == 0x0LL)
1362  return true;
1363  // Check if it can be encoded in an "ADD LSL #12".
1364  if ((ImmOff & 0xffffffffff000fffLL) == 0x0LL)
1365  // As a single MOVZ is faster than a "ADD of LSL #12", ignore such constant.
1366  return (ImmOff & 0xffffffffff00ffffLL) != 0x0LL &&
1367  (ImmOff & 0xffffffffffff0fffLL) != 0x0LL;
1368  return false;
1369 }
1370 
1371 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrModeXRO(SDValue N, unsigned Size,
1372  SDValue &Base, SDValue &Offset,
1373  SDValue &SignExtend,
1374  SDValue &DoShift) {
1375  if (N.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD)
1376  return false;
1377  SDValue LHS = N.getOperand(0);
1378  SDValue RHS = N.getOperand(1);
1379  SDLoc DL(N);
1380 
1381  // Check if this particular node is reused in any non-memory related
1382  // operation. If yes, do not try to fold this node into the address
1383  // computation, since the computation will be kept.
1384  const SDNode *Node = N.getNode();
1385  for (SDNode *UI : Node->uses()) {
1386  if (!isa<MemSDNode>(*UI))
1387  return false;
1388  }
1389 
1390  // Watch out if RHS is a wide immediate, it can not be selected into
1391  // [BaseReg+Imm] addressing mode. Also it may not be able to be encoded into
1392  // ADD/SUB. Instead it will use [BaseReg + 0] address mode and generate
1393  // instructions like:
1394  // MOV X0, WideImmediate
1395  // ADD X1, BaseReg, X0
1396  // LDR X2, [X1, 0]
1397  // For such situation, using [BaseReg, XReg] addressing mode can save one
1398  // ADD/SUB:
1399  // MOV X0, WideImmediate
1400  // LDR X2, [BaseReg, X0]
1401  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(RHS)) {
1402  int64_t ImmOff = (int64_t)cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS)->getZExtValue();
1403  unsigned Scale = Log2_32(Size);
1404  // Skip the immediate can be selected by load/store addressing mode.
1405  // Also skip the immediate can be encoded by a single ADD (SUB is also
1406  // checked by using -ImmOff).
1407  if ((ImmOff % Size == 0 && ImmOff >= 0 && ImmOff < (0x1000 << Scale)) ||
1408  isPreferredADD(ImmOff) || isPreferredADD(-ImmOff))
1409  return false;
1410 
1411  SDValue Ops[] = { RHS };
1412  SDNode *MOVI =
1413  CurDAG->getMachineNode(AArch64::MOVi64imm, DL, MVT::i64, Ops);
1414  SDValue MOVIV = SDValue(MOVI, 0);
1415  // This ADD of two X register will be selected into [Reg+Reg] mode.
1416  N = CurDAG->getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, MVT::i64, LHS, MOVIV);
1417  }
1418 
1419  // Remember if it is worth folding N when it produces extended register.
1420  bool IsExtendedRegisterWorthFolding = isWorthFolding(N);
1421 
1422  // Try to match a shifted extend on the RHS.
1423  if (IsExtendedRegisterWorthFolding && RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL &&
1424  SelectExtendedSHL(RHS, Size, false, Offset, SignExtend)) {
1425  Base = LHS;
1426  DoShift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(true, DL, MVT::i32);
1427  return true;
1428  }
1429 
1430  // Try to match a shifted extend on the LHS.
1431  if (IsExtendedRegisterWorthFolding && LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL &&
1432  SelectExtendedSHL(LHS, Size, false, Offset, SignExtend)) {
1433  Base = RHS;
1434  DoShift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(true, DL, MVT::i32);
1435  return true;
1436  }
1437 
1438  // Match any non-shifted, non-extend, non-immediate add expression.
1439  Base = LHS;
1440  Offset = RHS;
1441  SignExtend = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(false, DL, MVT::i32);
1442  DoShift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(false, DL, MVT::i32);
1443  // Reg1 + Reg2 is free: no check needed.
1444  return true;
1445 }
1446 
1447 SDValue AArch64DAGToDAGISel::createDTuple(ArrayRef<SDValue> Regs) {
1448  static const unsigned RegClassIDs[] = {
1449  AArch64::DDRegClassID, AArch64::DDDRegClassID, AArch64::DDDDRegClassID};
1450  static const unsigned SubRegs[] = {AArch64::dsub0, AArch64::dsub1,
1451  AArch64::dsub2, AArch64::dsub3};
1452 
1453  return createTuple(Regs, RegClassIDs, SubRegs);
1454 }

1456 SDValue AArch64DAGToDAGISel::createQTuple(ArrayRef<SDValue> Regs) {
1457  static const unsigned RegClassIDs[] = {
1458  AArch64::QQRegClassID, AArch64::QQQRegClassID, AArch64::QQQQRegClassID};
1459  static const unsigned SubRegs[] = {AArch64::qsub0, AArch64::qsub1,
1460  AArch64::qsub2, AArch64::qsub3};
1461 
1462  return createTuple(Regs, RegClassIDs, SubRegs);
1463 }

1465 SDValue AArch64DAGToDAGISel::createZTuple(ArrayRef<SDValue> Regs) {
1466  static const unsigned RegClassIDs[] = {AArch64::ZPR2RegClassID,
1467  AArch64::ZPR3RegClassID,
1468  AArch64::ZPR4RegClassID};
1469  static const unsigned SubRegs[] = {AArch64::zsub0, AArch64::zsub1,
1470  AArch64::zsub2, AArch64::zsub3};
1471 
1472  return createTuple(Regs, RegClassIDs, SubRegs);
1473 }
1474 
1475 SDValue AArch64DAGToDAGISel::createZMulTuple(ArrayRef<SDValue> Regs) {
1476  assert(Regs.size() == 2 || Regs.size() == 4);
1477 
1478  // The createTuple interface requires 3 RegClassIDs for each possible
1479  // tuple type even though we only have them for ZPR2 and ZPR4.
1480  static const unsigned RegClassIDs[] = {AArch64::ZPR2Mul2RegClassID, 0,
1481  AArch64::ZPR4Mul4RegClassID};
1482  static const unsigned SubRegs[] = {AArch64::zsub0, AArch64::zsub1,
1483  AArch64::zsub2, AArch64::zsub3};
1484  return createTuple(Regs, RegClassIDs, SubRegs);
1485 }
1486 
1487 SDValue AArch64DAGToDAGISel::createTuple(ArrayRef<SDValue> Regs,
1488  const unsigned RegClassIDs[],
1489  const unsigned SubRegs[]) {
1490  // There's no special register-class for a vector-list of 1 element: it's just
1491  // a vector.
1492  if (Regs.size() == 1)
1493  return Regs[0];
1494 
1495  assert(Regs.size() >= 2 && Regs.size() <= 4);
1496 
1497  SDLoc DL(Regs[0]);
1498 
1499  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Ops;
1500 
1501  // First operand of REG_SEQUENCE is the desired RegClass.
1502  Ops.push_back(
1503  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(RegClassIDs[Regs.size() - 2], DL, MVT::i32));
1504 
1505  // Then we get pairs of source & subregister-position for the components.
1506  for (unsigned i = 0; i < Regs.size(); ++i) {
1507  Ops.push_back(Regs[i]);
1508  Ops.push_back(CurDAG->getTargetConstant(SubRegs[i], DL, MVT::i32));
1509  }
1510 
1511  SDNode *N =
1512  CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, MVT::Untyped, Ops);
1513  return SDValue(N, 0);
1514 }
1515 
1516 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectTable(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs, unsigned Opc,
1517  bool isExt) {
1518  SDLoc dl(N);
1519  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1520 
1521  unsigned ExtOff = isExt;
1522 
1523  // Form a REG_SEQUENCE to force register allocation.
1524  unsigned Vec0Off = ExtOff + 1;
1525  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + Vec0Off,
1526  N->op_begin() + Vec0Off + NumVecs);
1527  SDValue RegSeq = createQTuple(Regs);
1528 
1529  SmallVector<SDValue, 6> Ops;
1530  if (isExt)
1531  Ops.push_back(N->getOperand(1));
1532  Ops.push_back(RegSeq);
1533  Ops.push_back(N->getOperand(NumVecs + ExtOff + 1));
1534  ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, VT, Ops));
1535 }
1536 
1537 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryIndexedLoad(SDNode *N) {
1538  LoadSDNode *LD = cast<LoadSDNode>(N);
1539  if (LD->isUnindexed())
1540  return false;
1541  EVT VT = LD->getMemoryVT();
1542  EVT DstVT = N->getValueType(0);
1543  ISD::MemIndexedMode AM = LD->getAddressingMode();
1544  bool IsPre = AM == ISD::PRE_INC || AM == ISD::PRE_DEC;
1545 
1546  // We're not doing validity checking here. That was done when checking
1547  // if we should mark the load as indexed or not. We're just selecting
1548  // the right instruction.
1549  unsigned Opcode = 0;
1550 
1551  ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = LD->getExtensionType();
1552  bool InsertTo64 = false;
1553  if (VT == MVT::i64)
1554  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRXpre : AArch64::LDRXpost;
1555  else if (VT == MVT::i32) {
1556  if (ExtType == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD)
1557  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRWpre : AArch64::LDRWpost;
1558  else if (ExtType == ISD::SEXTLOAD)
1559  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRSWpre : AArch64::LDRSWpost;
1560  else {
1561  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRWpre : AArch64::LDRWpost;
1562  InsertTo64 = true;
1563  // The result of the load is only i32. It's the subreg_to_reg that makes
1564  // it into an i64.
1565  DstVT = MVT::i32;
1566  }
1567  } else if (VT == MVT::i16) {
1568  if (ExtType == ISD::SEXTLOAD) {
1569  if (DstVT == MVT::i64)
1570  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRSHXpre : AArch64::LDRSHXpost;
1571  else
1572  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRSHWpre : AArch64::LDRSHWpost;
1573  } else {
1574  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRHHpre : AArch64::LDRHHpost;
1575  InsertTo64 = DstVT == MVT::i64;
1576  // The result of the load is only i32. It's the subreg_to_reg that makes
1577  // it into an i64.
1578  DstVT = MVT::i32;
1579  }
1580  } else if (VT == MVT::i8) {
1581  if (ExtType == ISD::SEXTLOAD) {
1582  if (DstVT == MVT::i64)
1583  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRSBXpre : AArch64::LDRSBXpost;
1584  else
1585  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRSBWpre : AArch64::LDRSBWpost;
1586  } else {
1587  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRBBpre : AArch64::LDRBBpost;
1588  InsertTo64 = DstVT == MVT::i64;
1589  // The result of the load is only i32. It's the subreg_to_reg that makes
1590  // it into an i64.
1591  DstVT = MVT::i32;
1592  }
1593  } else if (VT == MVT::f16) {
1594  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRHpre : AArch64::LDRHpost;
1595  } else if (VT == MVT::bf16) {
1596  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRHpre : AArch64::LDRHpost;
1597  } else if (VT == MVT::f32) {
1598  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRSpre : AArch64::LDRSpost;
1599  } else if (VT == MVT::f64 || VT.is64BitVector()) {
1600  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRDpre : AArch64::LDRDpost;
1601  } else if (VT.is128BitVector()) {
1602  Opcode = IsPre ? AArch64::LDRQpre : AArch64::LDRQpost;
1603  } else
1604  return false;
1605  SDValue Chain = LD->getChain();
1606  SDValue Base = LD->getBasePtr();
1607  ConstantSDNode *OffsetOp = cast<ConstantSDNode>(LD->getOffset());
1608  int OffsetVal = (int)OffsetOp->getZExtValue();
1609  SDLoc dl(N);
1610  SDValue Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(OffsetVal, dl, MVT::i64);
1611  SDValue Ops[] = { Base, Offset, Chain };
1612  SDNode *Res = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, dl, MVT::i64, DstVT,
1613  MVT::Other, Ops);
1614 
1615  // Transfer memoperands.
1616  MachineMemOperand *MemOp = cast<MemSDNode>(N)->getMemOperand();
1617  CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast<MachineSDNode>(Res), {MemOp});
1618 
1619  // Either way, we're replacing the node, so tell the caller that.
1620  SDValue LoadedVal = SDValue(Res, 1);
1621  if (InsertTo64) {
1622  SDValue SubReg = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::sub_32, dl, MVT::i32);
1623  LoadedVal =
1624  SDValue(CurDAG->getMachineNode(
1625  AArch64::SUBREG_TO_REG, dl, MVT::i64,
1626  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, dl, MVT::i64), LoadedVal,
1627  SubReg),
1628  0);
1629  }
1630 
1631  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 0), LoadedVal);
1632  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 1), SDValue(Res, 0));
1633  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 2), SDValue(Res, 2));
1634  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1635  return true;
1636 }
1637 
1638 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectLoad(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs, unsigned Opc,
1639  unsigned SubRegIdx) {
1640  SDLoc dl(N);
1641  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1642  SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
1643 
1644  SDValue Ops[] = {N->getOperand(2), // Mem operand;
1645  Chain};
1646 
1647  const EVT ResTys[] = {MVT::Untyped, MVT::Other};
1648 
1649  SDNode *Ld = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, ResTys, Ops);
1650  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Ld, 0);
1651  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVecs; ++i)
1652  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, i),
1653  CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(SubRegIdx + i, dl, VT, SuperReg));
1654 
1655  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, NumVecs), SDValue(Ld, 1));
1656 
1657  // Transfer memoperands. In the case of AArch64::LD64B, there won't be one,
1658  // because it's too simple to have needed special treatment during lowering.
1659  if (auto *MemIntr = dyn_cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(N)) {
1660  MachineMemOperand *MemOp = MemIntr->getMemOperand();
1661  CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast<MachineSDNode>(Ld), {MemOp});
1662  }
1663 
1664  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1665 }
1666 
1667 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectPostLoad(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
1668  unsigned Opc, unsigned SubRegIdx) {
1669  SDLoc dl(N);
1670  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1671  SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
1672 
1673  SDValue Ops[] = {N->getOperand(1), // Mem operand
1674  N->getOperand(2), // Incremental
1675  Chain};
1676 
1677  const EVT ResTys[] = {MVT::i64, // Type of the write back register
1678  MVT::Untyped, MVT::Other};
1679 
1680  SDNode *Ld = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, ResTys, Ops);
1681 
1682  // Update uses of write back register
1683  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, NumVecs), SDValue(Ld, 0));
1684 
1685  // Update uses of vector list
1686  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Ld, 1);
1687  if (NumVecs == 1)
1688  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 0), SuperReg);
1689  else
1690  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVecs; ++i)
1691  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, i),
1692  CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(SubRegIdx + i, dl, VT, SuperReg));
1693 
1694  // Update the chain
1695  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, NumVecs + 1), SDValue(Ld, 2));
1696  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1697 }
1698 
1699 /// Optimize \param OldBase and \param OldOffset selecting the best addressing
1700 /// mode. Returns a tuple consisting of an Opcode, an SDValue representing the
1701 /// new Base and an SDValue representing the new offset.
1702 std::tuple<unsigned, SDValue, SDValue>
1703 AArch64DAGToDAGISel::findAddrModeSVELoadStore(SDNode *N, unsigned Opc_rr,
1704  unsigned Opc_ri,
1705  const SDValue &OldBase,
1706  const SDValue &OldOffset,
1707  unsigned Scale) {
1708  SDValue NewBase = OldBase;
1709  SDValue NewOffset = OldOffset;
1710  // Detect a possible Reg+Imm addressing mode.
1711  const bool IsRegImm = SelectAddrModeIndexedSVE</*Min=*/-8, /*Max=*/7>(
1712  N, OldBase, NewBase, NewOffset);
1713 
1714  // Detect a possible reg+reg addressing mode, but only if we haven't already
1715  // detected a Reg+Imm one.
1716  const bool IsRegReg =
1717  !IsRegImm && SelectSVERegRegAddrMode(OldBase, Scale, NewBase, NewOffset);
1718 
1719  // Select the instruction.
1720  return std::make_tuple(IsRegReg ? Opc_rr : Opc_ri, NewBase, NewOffset);
1721 }
1722 
1723 enum class SelectTypeKind {
1724  Int1 = 0,
1725  Int = 1,
1726  FP = 2,
1727  AnyType = 3,
1728 };
1729 
1730 /// This function selects an opcode from a list of opcodes, which is
1731 /// expected to be the opcode for { 8-bit, 16-bit, 32-bit, 64-bit }
1732 /// element types, in this order.
1733 template <SelectTypeKind Kind>
1734 static unsigned SelectOpcodeFromVT(EVT VT, ArrayRef<unsigned> Opcodes) {
1735  // Only match scalable vector VTs
1736  if (!VT.isScalableVector())
1737  return 0;
1738 
1739  EVT EltVT = VT.getVectorElementType();
1740  switch (Kind) {
1741  case SelectTypeKind::AnyType:
1742  break;
1743  case SelectTypeKind::Int:
1744  if (EltVT != MVT::i8 && EltVT != MVT::i16 && EltVT != MVT::i32 &&
1745  EltVT != MVT::i64)
1746  return 0;
1747  break;
1748  case SelectTypeKind::Int1:
1749  if (EltVT != MVT::i1)
1750  return 0;
1751  break;
1752  case SelectTypeKind::FP:
1753  if (EltVT != MVT::f16 && EltVT != MVT::f32 && EltVT != MVT::f64)
1754  return 0;
1755  break;
1756  }
1757 
1758  unsigned Offset;
1759  switch (VT.getVectorMinNumElements()) {
1760  case 16: // 8-bit
1761  Offset = 0;
1762  break;
1763  case 8: // 16-bit
1764  Offset = 1;
1765  break;
1766  case 4: // 32-bit
1767  Offset = 2;
1768  break;
1769  case 2: // 64-bit
1770  Offset = 3;
1771  break;
1772  default:
1773  return 0;
1774  }
1775 
1776  return (Opcodes.size() <= Offset) ? 0 : Opcodes[Offset];
1777 }
1778 
1779 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectWhilePair(SDNode *N, unsigned Opc) {
1780  SDLoc DL(N);
1781  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1782 
1783  SDValue Ops[] = {N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2)};
1784 
1785  SDNode *WhilePair = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, DL, MVT::Untyped, Ops);
1786  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(WhilePair, 0);
1787 
1788  for (unsigned I = 0; I < 2; ++I)
1789  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, I), CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(
1790  AArch64::psub0 + I, DL, VT, SuperReg));
1791 
1792  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1793 }

1795 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectCVTIntrinsic(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
1796  unsigned Opcode) {
1797  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1798  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 1, N->op_begin() + 1 + NumVecs);
1799  SDValue Ops = createZTuple(Regs);
1800  SDLoc DL(N);
1801  SDNode *Intrinsic = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, MVT::Untyped, Ops);
1802  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Intrinsic, 0);
1803  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVecs; ++i)
1804  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, i), CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(
1805  AArch64::zsub0 + i, DL, VT, SuperReg));
1806 
1807  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1808  return;
1809 }

1811 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectDestructiveMultiIntrinsic(SDNode *N,
1812  unsigned NumVecs,
1813  bool IsZmMulti,
1814  unsigned Opcode) {
1815  assert(Opcode != 0 && "Unexpected opcode");
1816 
1817  SDLoc DL(N);
1818  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1819 
1820  auto GetMultiVecOperand = [=](unsigned StartIdx) {
1821  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + StartIdx,
1822  N->op_begin() + StartIdx + NumVecs);
1823  return createZMulTuple(Regs);
1824  };
1825 
1826  SDValue Zdn = GetMultiVecOperand(1);
1827 
1828  SDValue Zm;
1829  if (IsZmMulti)
1830  Zm = GetMultiVecOperand(NumVecs + 1);
1831  else
1832  Zm = N->getOperand(NumVecs + 1);
1833 
1834  SDNode *Intrinsic = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, MVT::Untyped, Zdn, Zm);
1835 
1836  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Intrinsic, 0);
1837  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVecs; ++i)
1838  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, i), CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(
1839  AArch64::zsub0 + i, DL, VT, SuperReg));
1840 
1841  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1842  return;
1843 }

1845 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectPredicatedLoad(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
1846  unsigned Scale, unsigned Opc_ri,
1847  unsigned Opc_rr, bool IsIntr) {
1848  assert(Scale < 4 && "Invalid scaling value.");
1849  SDLoc DL(N);
1850  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1851  SDValue Chain = N->getOperand(0);
1852 
1853  // Optimize addressing mode.
1854  SDValue Base, Offset;
1855  unsigned Opc;
1856  std::tie(Opc, Base, Offset) = findAddrModeSVELoadStore(
1857  N, Opc_rr, Opc_ri, N->getOperand(IsIntr ? 3 : 2),
1858  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i64), Scale);
1859 
1860  SDValue Ops[] = {N->getOperand(IsIntr ? 2 : 1), // Predicate
1861  Base, // Memory operand
1862  Offset, Chain};
1863 
1864  const EVT ResTys[] = {MVT::Untyped, MVT::Other};
1865 
1866  SDNode *Load = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, DL, ResTys, Ops);
1867  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Load, 0);
1868  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVecs; ++i)
1869  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, i), CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(
1870  AArch64::zsub0 + i, DL, VT, SuperReg));
1871 
1872  // Copy chain
1873  unsigned ChainIdx = NumVecs;
1874  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, ChainIdx), SDValue(Load, 1));
1875  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1876 }

1879  unsigned Opcode) {
1880  if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::nxv4f32)
1881  return;
1882  SelectUnaryMultiIntrinsic(N, NumVecs, true, Opcode);
1883 }

1885 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectClamp(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
1886  unsigned Op) {
1887  SDLoc DL(N);
1888  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1889 
1890  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 1, N->op_begin() + 1 + NumVecs);
1891  SDValue Zd = createZMulTuple(Regs);
1892  SDValue Zn = N->getOperand(1 + NumVecs);
1893  SDValue Zm = N->getOperand(2 + NumVecs);
1894 
1895  SDValue Ops[] = {Zd, Zn, Zm};
1896 
1897  SDNode *Intrinsic = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Op, DL, MVT::Untyped, Ops);
1898  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Intrinsic, 0);
1899  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVecs; ++i)
1900  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, i), CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(
1901  AArch64::zsub0 + i, DL, VT, SuperReg));
1902 
1903  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1904  return;
1905 }

1907 bool SelectSMETile(unsigned &BaseReg, unsigned TileNum) {
1908  switch (BaseReg) {
1909  default:
1910  return false;
1911  case AArch64::ZA:
1912  case AArch64::ZAB0:
1913  if (TileNum == 0)
1914  break;
1915  return false;
1916  case AArch64::ZAH0:
1917  if (TileNum <= 1)
1918  break;
1919  return false;
1920  case AArch64::ZAS0:
1921  if (TileNum <= 3)
1922  break;
1923  return false;
1924  case AArch64::ZAD0:
1925  if (TileNum <= 7)
1926  break;
1927  return false;
1928  }
1929 
1930  BaseReg += TileNum;
1931  return true;
1932 }
1933 
1934 template <unsigned MaxIdx, unsigned Scale>
1935 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectMultiVectorMove(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
1936  unsigned BaseReg, unsigned Op) {
1937  unsigned TileNum = 0;
1938  if (BaseReg != AArch64::ZA)
1939  TileNum = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(2))->getZExtValue();
1940 
1941  if (!SelectSMETile(BaseReg, TileNum))
1942  return;
1943 
1944  SDValue SliceBase, Base, Offset;
1945  if (BaseReg == AArch64::ZA)
1946  SliceBase = N->getOperand(2);
1947  else
1948  SliceBase = N->getOperand(3);
1949 
1950  if (!SelectSMETileSlice(SliceBase, MaxIdx, Base, Offset, Scale))
1951  return;
1952 
1953  SDLoc DL(N);
1954  SDValue SubReg = CurDAG->getRegister(BaseReg, MVT::Other);
1955  SDValue Ops[] = {SubReg, Base, Offset, /*Chain*/ N->getOperand(0)};
1956  SDNode *Mov = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Op, DL, {MVT::Untyped, MVT::Other}, Ops);
1957 
1958  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1959  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumVecs; ++I)
1960  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, I),
1961  CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(AArch64::zsub0 + I, DL, VT,
1962  SDValue(Mov, 0)));
1963  // Copy chain
1964  unsigned ChainIdx = NumVecs;
1965  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, ChainIdx), SDValue(Mov, 1));
1966  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1967 }
1968 
1969 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectUnaryMultiIntrinsic(SDNode *N,
1970  unsigned NumOutVecs,
1971  bool IsTupleInput,
1972  unsigned Opc) {
1973  SDLoc DL(N);
1974  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
1975  unsigned NumInVecs = N->getNumOperands() - 1;
1976 
1977  SmallVector<SDValue, 6> Ops;
1978  if (IsTupleInput) {
1979  assert((NumInVecs == 2 || NumInVecs == 4) &&
1980  "Don't know how to handle multi-register input!");
1981  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 1,
1982  N->op_begin() + 1 + NumInVecs);
1983  Ops.push_back(createZMulTuple(Regs));
1984  } else {
1985  // All intrinsic nodes have the ID as the first operand, hence the "1 + I".
1986  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumInVecs; I++)
1987  Ops.push_back(N->getOperand(1 + I));
1988  }
1989 
1990  SDNode *Res = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, DL, MVT::Untyped, Ops);
1991  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Res, 0);
1992 
1993  for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumOutVecs; I++)
1994  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, I), CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(
1995  AArch64::zsub0 + I, DL, VT, SuperReg));
1996  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
1997 }

1999 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectStore(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
2000  unsigned Opc) {
2001  SDLoc dl(N);
2002  EVT VT = N->getOperand(2)->getValueType(0);
2003 
2004  // Form a REG_SEQUENCE to force register allocation.
2005  bool Is128Bit = VT.getSizeInBits() == 128;
2006  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 2, N->op_begin() + 2 + NumVecs);
2007  SDValue RegSeq = Is128Bit ? createQTuple(Regs) : createDTuple(Regs);
2008 
2009  SDValue Ops[] = {RegSeq, N->getOperand(NumVecs + 2), N->getOperand(0)};
2010  SDNode *St = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), Ops);
2011 
2012  // Transfer memoperands.
2013  MachineMemOperand *MemOp = cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(N)->getMemOperand();
2014  CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast<MachineSDNode>(St), {MemOp});
2015 
2016  ReplaceNode(N, St);
2017 }

2019 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectPredicatedStore(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
2020  unsigned Scale, unsigned Opc_rr,
2021  unsigned Opc_ri) {
2022  SDLoc dl(N);
2023 
2024  // Form a REG_SEQUENCE to force register allocation.
2025  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 2, N->op_begin() + 2 + NumVecs);
2026  SDValue RegSeq = createZTuple(Regs);
2027 
2028  // Optimize addressing mode.
2029  unsigned Opc;
2030  SDValue Offset, Base;
2031  std::tie(Opc, Base, Offset) = findAddrModeSVELoadStore(
2032  N, Opc_rr, Opc_ri, N->getOperand(NumVecs + 3),
2033  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, dl, MVT::i64), Scale);
2034 
2035  SDValue Ops[] = {RegSeq, N->getOperand(NumVecs + 2), // predicate
2036  Base, // address
2037  Offset, // offset
2038  N->getOperand(0)}; // chain
2039  SDNode *St = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, N->getValueType(0), Ops);
2040 
2041  ReplaceNode(N, St);
2042 }

2044 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrModeFrameIndexSVE(SDValue N, SDValue &Base,
2045  SDValue &OffImm) {
2046  SDLoc dl(N);
2047  const DataLayout &DL = CurDAG->getDataLayout();
2048  const TargetLowering *TLI = getTargetLowering();
2049 
2050  // Try to match it for the frame address
2051  if (auto FINode = dyn_cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(N)) {
2052  int FI = FINode->getIndex();
2053  Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI, TLI->getPointerTy(DL));
2054  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, dl, MVT::i64);
2055  return true;
2056  }
2057 
2058  return false;
2059 }

2061 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectPostStore(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
2062  unsigned Opc) {
2063  SDLoc dl(N);
2064  EVT VT = N->getOperand(2)->getValueType(0);
2065  const EVT ResTys[] = {MVT::i64, // Type of the write back register
2066  MVT::Other}; // Type for the Chain
2067 
2068  // Form a REG_SEQUENCE to force register allocation.
2069  bool Is128Bit = VT.getSizeInBits() == 128;
2070  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 1, N->op_begin() + 1 + NumVecs);
2071  SDValue RegSeq = Is128Bit ? createQTuple(Regs) : createDTuple(Regs);
2072 
2073  SDValue Ops[] = {RegSeq,
2074  N->getOperand(NumVecs + 1), // base register
2075  N->getOperand(NumVecs + 2), // Incremental
2076  N->getOperand(0)}; // Chain
2077  SDNode *St = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, ResTys, Ops);
2078 
2079  ReplaceNode(N, St);
2080 }

2082 namespace {
2083 /// WidenVector - Given a value in the V64 register class, produce the
2084 /// equivalent value in the V128 register class.
2085 class WidenVector {
2086  SelectionDAG &DAG;
2087 
2088 public:
2089  WidenVector(SelectionDAG &DAG) : DAG(DAG) {}
2090 
2091  SDValue operator()(SDValue V64Reg) {
2092  EVT VT = V64Reg.getValueType();
2093  unsigned NarrowSize = VT.getVectorNumElements();
2094  MVT EltTy = VT.getVectorElementType().getSimpleVT();
2095  MVT WideTy = MVT::getVectorVT(EltTy, 2 * NarrowSize);
2096  SDLoc DL(V64Reg);
2097 
2098  SDValue Undef =
2099  SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF, DL, WideTy), 0);
2100  return DAG.getTargetInsertSubreg(AArch64::dsub, DL, WideTy, Undef, V64Reg);
2101  }
2102 };
2103 } // namespace
2104 
2105 /// NarrowVector - Given a value in the V128 register class, produce the
2106 /// equivalent value in the V64 register class.
2107 static SDValue NarrowVector(SDValue V128Reg, SelectionDAG &DAG) {
2108  EVT VT = V128Reg.getValueType();
2109  unsigned WideSize = VT.getVectorNumElements();
2110  MVT EltTy = VT.getVectorElementType().getSimpleVT();
2111  MVT NarrowTy = MVT::getVectorVT(EltTy, WideSize / 2);
2112 
2113  return DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(AArch64::dsub, SDLoc(V128Reg), NarrowTy,
2114  V128Reg);
2115 }
2116 
2117 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectLoadLane(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
2118  unsigned Opc) {
2119  SDLoc dl(N);
2120  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2121  bool Narrow = VT.getSizeInBits() == 64;
2122 
2123  // Form a REG_SEQUENCE to force register allocation.
2124  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 2, N->op_begin() + 2 + NumVecs);
2125 
2126  if (Narrow)
2127  transform(Regs, Regs.begin(),
2128  WidenVector(*CurDAG));
2129 
2130  SDValue RegSeq = createQTuple(Regs);
2131 
2132  const EVT ResTys[] = {MVT::Untyped, MVT::Other};
2133 
2134  unsigned LaneNo =
2135  cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(NumVecs + 2))->getZExtValue();
2136 
2137  SDValue Ops[] = {RegSeq, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LaneNo, dl, MVT::i64),
2138  N->getOperand(NumVecs + 3), N->getOperand(0)};
2139  SDNode *Ld = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, ResTys, Ops);
2140  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Ld, 0);
2141 
2142  EVT WideVT = RegSeq.getOperand(1)->getValueType(0);
2143  static const unsigned QSubs[] = { AArch64::qsub0, AArch64::qsub1,
2144  AArch64::qsub2, AArch64::qsub3 };
2145  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVecs; ++i) {
2146  SDValue NV = CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(QSubs[i], dl, WideVT, SuperReg);
2147  if (Narrow)
2148  NV = NarrowVector(NV, *CurDAG);
2149  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, i), NV);
2150  }
2151 
2152  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, NumVecs), SDValue(Ld, 1));
2153  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
2154 }
2155 
2156 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectPostLoadLane(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
2157  unsigned Opc) {
2158  SDLoc dl(N);
2159  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2160  bool Narrow = VT.getSizeInBits() == 64;
2161 
2162  // Form a REG_SEQUENCE to force register allocation.
2163  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 1, N->op_begin() + 1 + NumVecs);
2164 
2165  if (Narrow)
2166  transform(Regs, Regs.begin(),
2167  WidenVector(*CurDAG));
2168 
2169  SDValue RegSeq = createQTuple(Regs);
2170 
2171  const EVT ResTys[] = {MVT::i64, // Type of the write back register
2172  RegSeq->getValueType(0), MVT::Other};
2173 
2174  unsigned LaneNo =
2175  cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(NumVecs + 1))->getZExtValue();
2176 
2177  SDValue Ops[] = {RegSeq,
2178  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LaneNo, dl,
2179  MVT::i64), // Lane Number
2180  N->getOperand(NumVecs + 2), // Base register
2181  N->getOperand(NumVecs + 3), // Incremental
2182  N->getOperand(0)};
2183  SDNode *Ld = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, ResTys, Ops);
2184 
2185  // Update uses of the write back register
2186  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, NumVecs), SDValue(Ld, 0));
2187 
2188  // Update uses of the vector list
2189  SDValue SuperReg = SDValue(Ld, 1);
2190  if (NumVecs == 1) {
2191  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 0),
2192  Narrow ? NarrowVector(SuperReg, *CurDAG) : SuperReg);
2193  } else {
2194  EVT WideVT = RegSeq.getOperand(1)->getValueType(0);
2195  static const unsigned QSubs[] = { AArch64::qsub0, AArch64::qsub1,
2196  AArch64::qsub2, AArch64::qsub3 };
2197  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVecs; ++i) {
2198  SDValue NV = CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(QSubs[i], dl, WideVT,
2199  SuperReg);
2200  if (Narrow)
2201  NV = NarrowVector(NV, *CurDAG);
2202  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, i), NV);
2203  }
2204  }
2205 
2206  // Update the Chain
2207  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, NumVecs + 1), SDValue(Ld, 2));
2208  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
2209 }
2210 
2211 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectStoreLane(SDNode *N, unsigned NumVecs,
2212  unsigned Opc) {
2213  SDLoc dl(N);
2214  EVT VT = N->getOperand(2)->getValueType(0);
2215  bool Narrow = VT.getSizeInBits() == 64;
2216 
2217  // Form a REG_SEQUENCE to force register allocation.
2218  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 2, N->op_begin() + 2 + NumVecs);
2219 
2220  if (Narrow)
2221  transform(Regs, Regs.begin(),
2222  WidenVector(*CurDAG));
2223 
2224  SDValue RegSeq = createQTuple(Regs);
2225 
2226  unsigned LaneNo =
2227  cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(NumVecs + 2))->getZExtValue();
2228 
2229  SDValue Ops[] = {RegSeq, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LaneNo, dl, MVT::i64),
2230  N->getOperand(NumVecs + 3), N->getOperand(0)};
2231  SDNode *St = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, MVT::Other, Ops);
2232 
2233  // Transfer memoperands.
2234  MachineMemOperand *MemOp = cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(N)->getMemOperand();
2235  CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast<MachineSDNode>(St), {MemOp});
2236 
2237  ReplaceNode(N, St);
2238 }

2241  unsigned Opc) {

2244  bool Narrow = VT.getSizeInBits() == 64;
2245

2247  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Regs(N->op_begin() + 1, N->op_begin() + 1 + NumVecs);
2248 
2249  if (Narrow)
2250  transform(Regs, Regs.begin(),
2251  WidenVector(*CurDAG));
2252

2256  MVT::Other};

2259  cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(NumVecs + 1))->getZExtValue();
