2273 
2274 static bool isBitfieldExtractOpFromAnd(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDNode *N,
2275  unsigned &Opc, SDValue &Opd0,
2276  unsigned &LSB, unsigned &MSB,
2277  unsigned NumberOfIgnoredLowBits,
2278  bool BiggerPattern) {
2279  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::AND &&
2280  "N must be a AND operation to call this function");
2281 
2282  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2283 
2284  // Here we can test the type of VT and return false when the type does not
2285  // match, but since it is done prior to that call in the current context
2286  // we turned that into an assert to avoid redundant code.
2287  assert((VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64) &&
2288  "Type checking must have been done before calling this function");
2289 
2290  // FIXME: simplify-demanded-bits in DAGCombine will probably have
2291  // changed the AND node to a 32-bit mask operation. We'll have to
2292  // undo that as part of the transform here if we want to catch all
2293  // the opportunities.
2294  // Currently the NumberOfIgnoredLowBits argument helps to recover
2295  // from these situations when matching bigger pattern (bitfield insert).
2296 
2297  // For unsigned extracts, check for a shift right and mask
2298  uint64_t AndImm = 0;
2299  if (!isOpcWithIntImmediate(N, ISD::AND, AndImm))
2300  return false;
2301 
2302  const SDNode *Op0 = N->getOperand(0).getNode();
2303 
2304  // Because of simplify-demanded-bits in DAGCombine, the mask may have been
2305  // simplified. Try to undo that
2306  AndImm |= maskTrailingOnes<uint64_t>(NumberOfIgnoredLowBits);
2307 
2308  // The immediate is a mask of the low bits iff imm & (imm+1) == 0
2309  if (AndImm & (AndImm + 1))
2310  return false;
2311 
2312  bool ClampMSB = false;
2313  uint64_t SrlImm = 0;
2314  // Handle the SRL + ANY_EXTEND case.
2315  if (VT == MVT::i64 && Op0->getOpcode() == ISD::ANY_EXTEND &&
2316  isOpcWithIntImmediate(Op0->getOperand(0).getNode(), ISD::SRL, SrlImm)) {
2317  // Extend the incoming operand of the SRL to 64-bit.
2318  Opd0 = Widen(CurDAG, Op0->getOperand(0).getOperand(0));
2319  // Make sure to clamp the MSB so that we preserve the semantics of the
2320  // original operations.
2321  ClampMSB = true;
2322  } else if (VT == MVT::i32 && Op0->getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE &&
2323  isOpcWithIntImmediate(Op0->getOperand(0).getNode(), ISD::SRL,
2324  SrlImm)) {
2325  // If the shift result was truncated, we can still combine them.
2326  Opd0 = Op0->getOperand(0).getOperand(0);
2327 
2328  // Use the type of SRL node.
2329  VT = Opd0->getValueType(0);
2330  } else if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(Op0, ISD::SRL, SrlImm)) {
2331  Opd0 = Op0->getOperand(0);
2332  ClampMSB = (VT == MVT::i32);
2333  } else if (BiggerPattern) {
2334  // Let's pretend a 0 shift right has been performed.
2335  // The resulting code will be at least as good as the original one
2336  // plus it may expose more opportunities for bitfield insert pattern.
2337  // FIXME: Currently we limit this to the bigger pattern, because
2338  // some optimizations expect AND and not UBFM.
2339  Opd0 = N->getOperand(0);
2340  } else
2341  return false;
2342 
2343  // Bail out on large immediates. This happens when no proper
2344  // combining/constant folding was performed.
2345  if (!BiggerPattern && (SrlImm <= 0 || SrlImm >= VT.getSizeInBits())) {
2346  LLVM_DEBUG(
2347  (dbgs() << N
2348  << ": Found large shift immediate, this should not happen\n"));
2349  return false;
2350  }
2351 
2352  LSB = SrlImm;
2353  MSB = SrlImm +
2354  (VT == MVT::i32 ? llvm::countr_one<uint32_t>(AndImm)
2355  : llvm::countr_one<uint64_t>(AndImm)) -
2356  1;
2357  if (ClampMSB)
2358  // Since we're moving the extend before the right shift operation, we need
2359  // to clamp the MSB to make sure we don't shift in undefined bits instead of
2360  // the zeros which would get shifted in with the original right shift
2361  // operation.
2362  MSB = MSB > 31 ? 31 : MSB;
2363 
2364  Opc = VT == MVT::i32 ? AArch64::UBFMWri : AArch64::UBFMXri;
2365  return true;
2366 }
2367 
2368 static bool isBitfieldExtractOpFromSExtInReg(SDNode *N, unsigned &Opc,
2369  SDValue &Opd0, unsigned &Immr,
2370  unsigned &Imms) {
2371  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG);
2372 
2373  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2374  unsigned BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
2375  assert((VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64) &&
2376  "Type checking must have been done before calling this function");
2377 
2378  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
2379  if (Op->getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE) {
2380  Op = Op->getOperand(0);
2381  VT = Op->getValueType(0);
2382  BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
2383  }
2384 
2385  uint64_t ShiftImm;
2386  if (!isOpcWithIntImmediate(Op.getNode(), ISD::SRL, ShiftImm) &&
2387  !isOpcWithIntImmediate(Op.getNode(), ISD::SRA, ShiftImm))
2388  return false;
2389 
2390  unsigned Width = cast<VTSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getVT().getSizeInBits();
2391  if (ShiftImm + Width > BitWidth)
2392  return false;
2393 
2394  Opc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::SBFMWri : AArch64::SBFMXri;
2395  Opd0 = Op.getOperand(0);
2396  Immr = ShiftImm;
2397  Imms = ShiftImm + Width - 1;
2398  return true;
2399 }
2400 
2401 static bool isSeveralBitsExtractOpFromShr(SDNode *N, unsigned &Opc,
2402  SDValue &Opd0, unsigned &LSB,
2403  unsigned &MSB) {
2404  // We are looking for the following pattern which basically extracts several
2405  // continuous bits from the source value and places it from the LSB of the
2406  // destination value, all other bits of the destination value or set to zero:
2407  //
2408  // Value2 = AND Value, MaskImm
2409  // SRL Value2, ShiftImm
2410  //
2411  // with MaskImm >> ShiftImm to search for the bit width.
2412  //
2413  // This gets selected into a single UBFM:
2414  //
2415  // UBFM Value, ShiftImm, Log2_64(MaskImm)
2416  //
2417 
2418  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::SRL)
2419  return false;
2420 
2421  uint64_t AndMask = 0;
2422  if (!isOpcWithIntImmediate(N->getOperand(0).getNode(), ISD::AND, AndMask))
2423  return false;
2424 
2425  Opd0 = N->getOperand(0).getOperand(0);
2426 
2427  uint64_t SrlImm = 0;
2428  if (!isIntImmediate(N->getOperand(1), SrlImm))
2429  return false;
2430 
2431  // Check whether we really have several bits extract here.
2432  if (!isMask_64(AndMask >> SrlImm))
2433  return false;
2434 
2435  Opc = N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32 ? AArch64::UBFMWri : AArch64::UBFMXri;
2436  LSB = SrlImm;
2437  MSB = llvm::Log2_64(AndMask);
2438  return true;
2439 }
2440 
2441 static bool isBitfieldExtractOpFromShr(SDNode *N, unsigned &Opc, SDValue &Opd0,
2442  unsigned &Immr, unsigned &Imms,
2443  bool BiggerPattern) {
2444  assert((N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA || N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL) &&
2445  "N must be a SHR/SRA operation to call this function");
2446 
2447  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2448 
2449  // Here we can test the type of VT and return false when the type does not
2450  // match, but since it is done prior to that call in the current context
2451  // we turned that into an assert to avoid redundant code.
2452  assert((VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64) &&
2453  "Type checking must have been done before calling this function");
2454 
2455  // Check for AND + SRL doing several bits extract.
2456  if (isSeveralBitsExtractOpFromShr(N, Opc, Opd0, Immr, Imms))
2457  return true;
2458 
2459  // We're looking for a shift of a shift.
2460  uint64_t ShlImm = 0;
2461  uint64_t TruncBits = 0;
2462  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(N->getOperand(0).getNode(), ISD::SHL, ShlImm)) {
2463  Opd0 = N->getOperand(0).getOperand(0);
2464  } else if (VT == MVT::i32 && N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL &&
2465  N->getOperand(0).getNode()->getOpcode() == ISD::TRUNCATE) {
2466  // We are looking for a shift of truncate. Truncate from i64 to i32 could
2467  // be considered as setting high 32 bits as zero. Our strategy here is to
2468  // always generate 64bit UBFM. This consistency will help the CSE pass
2469  // later find more redundancy.
2470  Opd0 = N->getOperand(0).getOperand(0);
2471  TruncBits = Opd0->getValueType(0).getSizeInBits() - VT.getSizeInBits();
2472  VT = Opd0.getValueType();
2473  assert(VT == MVT::i64 && "the promoted type should be i64");
2474  } else if (BiggerPattern) {
2475  // Let's pretend a 0 shift left has been performed.
2476  // FIXME: Currently we limit this to the bigger pattern case,
2477  // because some optimizations expect AND and not UBFM
2478  Opd0 = N->getOperand(0);
2479  } else
2480  return false;
2481 
2482  // Missing combines/constant folding may have left us with strange
2483  // constants.
2484  if (ShlImm >= VT.getSizeInBits()) {
2485  LLVM_DEBUG(
2486  (dbgs() << N
2487  << ": Found large shift immediate, this should not happen\n"));
2488  return false;
2489  }
2490 
2491  uint64_t SrlImm = 0;
2492  if (!isIntImmediate(N->getOperand(1), SrlImm))
2493  return false;
2494 
2495  assert(SrlImm > 0 && SrlImm < VT.getSizeInBits() &&
2496  "bad amount in shift node!");
2497  int immr = SrlImm - ShlImm;
2498  Immr = immr < 0 ? immr + VT.getSizeInBits() : immr;
2499  Imms = VT.getSizeInBits() - ShlImm - TruncBits - 1;
2500  // SRA requires a signed extraction
2501  if (VT == MVT::i32)
2502  Opc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA ? AArch64::SBFMWri : AArch64::UBFMWri;
2503  else
2504  Opc = N->getOpcode() == ISD::SRA ? AArch64::SBFMXri : AArch64::UBFMXri;
2505  return true;
2506 }
2507 
2508 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryBitfieldExtractOpFromSExt(SDNode *N) {
2509  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND);
2510 
2511  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2512  EVT NarrowVT = N->getOperand(0)->getValueType(0);
2513  if (VT != MVT::i64 || NarrowVT != MVT::i32)
2514  return false;
2515 
2516  uint64_t ShiftImm;
2517  SDValue Op = N->getOperand(0);
2518  if (!isOpcWithIntImmediate(Op.getNode(), ISD::SRA, ShiftImm))
2519  return false;
2520 
2521  SDLoc dl(N);
2522  // Extend the incoming operand of the shift to 64-bits.
2523  SDValue Opd0 = Widen(CurDAG, Op.getOperand(0));
2524  unsigned Immr = ShiftImm;
2525  unsigned Imms = NarrowVT.getSizeInBits() - 1;
2526  SDValue Ops[] = {Opd0, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Immr, dl, VT),
2527  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Imms, dl, VT)};
2528  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, AArch64::SBFMXri, VT, Ops);
2529  return true;
2530 }
2531 
2532 /// Try to form fcvtl2 instructions from a floating-point extend of a high-half
2533 /// extract of a subvector.
2534 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryHighFPExt(SDNode *N) {
2535  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::FP_EXTEND);
2536 
2537  // There are 2 forms of fcvtl2 - extend to double or extend to float.
2538  SDValue Extract = N->getOperand(0);
2539  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2540  EVT NarrowVT = Extract.getValueType();
2541  if ((VT != MVT::v2f64 || NarrowVT != MVT::v2f32) &&
2542  (VT != MVT::v4f32 || NarrowVT != MVT::v4f16))
2543  return false;
2544 
2545  // Optionally look past a bitcast.
2546  Extract = peekThroughBitcasts(Extract);
2547  if (Extract.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR)
2548  return false;
2549 
2550  // Match extract from start of high half index.
2551  // Example: v8i16 -> v4i16 means the extract must begin at index 4.
2552  unsigned ExtractIndex = Extract.getConstantOperandVal(1);
2553  if (ExtractIndex != Extract.getValueType().getVectorNumElements())
2554  return false;
2555 
2556  auto Opcode = VT == MVT::v2f64 ? AArch64::FCVTLv4i32 : AArch64::FCVTLv8i16;
2557  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opcode, VT, Extract.getOperand(0));
2558  return true;
2559 }
2560 
2561 static bool isBitfieldExtractOp(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDNode *N, unsigned &Opc,
2562  SDValue &Opd0, unsigned &Immr, unsigned &Imms,
2563  unsigned NumberOfIgnoredLowBits = 0,
2564  bool BiggerPattern = false) {
2565  if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i32 && N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i64)
2566  return false;
2567 
2568  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
2569  default:
2570  if (!N->isMachineOpcode())
2571  return false;
2572  break;
2573  case ISD::AND:
2574  return isBitfieldExtractOpFromAnd(CurDAG, N, Opc, Opd0, Immr, Imms,
2575  NumberOfIgnoredLowBits, BiggerPattern);
2576  case ISD::SRL:
2577  case ISD::SRA:
2578  return isBitfieldExtractOpFromShr(N, Opc, Opd0, Immr, Imms, BiggerPattern);
2579 
2580  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
2581  return isBitfieldExtractOpFromSExtInReg(N, Opc, Opd0, Immr, Imms);
2582  }
2583 
2584  unsigned NOpc = N->getMachineOpcode();
2585  switch (NOpc) {
2586  default:
2587  return false;
2588  case AArch64::SBFMWri:
2589  case AArch64::UBFMWri:
2590  case AArch64::SBFMXri:
2591  case AArch64::UBFMXri:
2592  Opc = NOpc;
2593  Opd0 = N->getOperand(0);
2594  Immr = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1).getNode())->getZExtValue();
2595  Imms = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(2).getNode())->getZExtValue();
2596  return true;
2597  }
2598  // Unreachable
2599  return false;
2600 }
2601 
2602 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryBitfieldExtractOp(SDNode *N) {
2603  unsigned Opc, Immr, Imms;
2604  SDValue Opd0;
2605  if (!isBitfieldExtractOp(CurDAG, N, Opc, Opd0, Immr, Imms))
2606  return false;
2607 
2608  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
2609  SDLoc dl(N);
2610 
2611  // If the bit extract operation is 64bit but the original type is 32bit, we
2612  // need to add one EXTRACT_SUBREG.
2613  if ((Opc == AArch64::SBFMXri || Opc == AArch64::UBFMXri) && VT == MVT::i32) {
2614  SDValue Ops64[] = {Opd0, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Immr, dl, MVT::i64),
2615  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Imms, dl, MVT::i64)};
2616 
2617  SDNode *BFM = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Opc, dl, MVT::i64, Ops64);
2618  SDValue SubReg = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::sub_32, dl, MVT::i32);
2619  ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG, dl,
2620  MVT::i32, SDValue(BFM, 0), SubReg));
2621  return true;
2622  }
2623 
2624  SDValue Ops[] = {Opd0, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Immr, dl, VT),
2625  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Imms, dl, VT)};
2626  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, VT, Ops);
2627  return true;
2628 }
2629 
2630 /// Does DstMask form a complementary pair with the mask provided by
2631 /// BitsToBeInserted, suitable for use in a BFI instruction. Roughly speaking,
2632 /// this asks whether DstMask zeroes precisely those bits that will be set by
2633 /// the other half.
2634 static bool isBitfieldDstMask(uint64_t DstMask, const APInt &BitsToBeInserted,
2635  unsigned NumberOfIgnoredHighBits, EVT VT) {
2636  assert((VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64) &&
2637  "i32 or i64 mask type expected!");
2638  unsigned BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits() - NumberOfIgnoredHighBits;
2639 
2640  APInt SignificantDstMask = APInt(BitWidth, DstMask);
2641  APInt SignificantBitsToBeInserted = BitsToBeInserted.zextOrTrunc(BitWidth);
2642 
2643  return (SignificantDstMask & SignificantBitsToBeInserted) == 0 &&
2644  (SignificantDstMask | SignificantBitsToBeInserted).isAllOnes();
2645 }
2646 
2647 // Look for bits that will be useful for later uses.
2648 // A bit is consider useless as soon as it is dropped and never used
2649 // before it as been dropped.
2650 // E.g., looking for useful bit of x
2651 // 1. y = x & 0x7
2652 // 2. z = y >> 2
2653 // After #1, x useful bits are 0x7, then the useful bits of x, live through
2654 // y.
2655 // After #2, the useful bits of x are 0x4.
2656 // However, if x is used on an unpredicatable instruction, then all its bits
2657 // are useful.
2658 // E.g.
2659 // 1. y = x & 0x7
2660 // 2. z = y >> 2
2661 // 3. str x, [@x]
2662 static void getUsefulBits(SDValue Op, APInt &UsefulBits, unsigned Depth = 0);
2663 
2664 static void getUsefulBitsFromAndWithImmediate(SDValue Op, APInt &UsefulBits,
2665  unsigned Depth) {
2666  uint64_t Imm =
2667  cast<const ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1).getNode())->getZExtValue();
2668  Imm = AArch64_AM::decodeLogicalImmediate(Imm, UsefulBits.getBitWidth());
2669  UsefulBits &= APInt(UsefulBits.getBitWidth(), Imm);
2670  getUsefulBits(Op, UsefulBits, Depth + 1);
2671 }
2672 
2673 static void getUsefulBitsFromBitfieldMoveOpd(SDValue Op, APInt &UsefulBits,
2674  uint64_t Imm, uint64_t MSB,
2675  unsigned Depth) {
2676  // inherit the bitwidth value
2677  APInt OpUsefulBits(UsefulBits);
2678  OpUsefulBits = 1;
2679 
2680  if (MSB >= Imm) {
2681  OpUsefulBits <<= MSB - Imm + 1;
2682  --OpUsefulBits;
2683  // The interesting part will be in the lower part of the result
2684  getUsefulBits(Op, OpUsefulBits, Depth + 1);
2685  // The interesting part was starting at Imm in the argument
2686  OpUsefulBits <<= Imm;
2687  } else {
2688  OpUsefulBits <<= MSB + 1;
2689  --OpUsefulBits;
2690  // The interesting part will be shifted in the result
2691  OpUsefulBits <<= OpUsefulBits.getBitWidth() - Imm;
2692  getUsefulBits(Op, OpUsefulBits, Depth + 1);
2693  // The interesting part was at zero in the argument
2694  OpUsefulBits.lshrInPlace(OpUsefulBits.getBitWidth() - Imm);
2695  }
2696 
2697  UsefulBits &= OpUsefulBits;
2698 }
2699 
2700 static void getUsefulBitsFromUBFM(SDValue Op, APInt &UsefulBits,
2701  unsigned Depth) {
2702  uint64_t Imm =
2703  cast<const ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1).getNode())->getZExtValue();
2704  uint64_t MSB =
2705  cast<const ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2).getNode())->getZExtValue();
2706 
2707  getUsefulBitsFromBitfieldMoveOpd(Op, UsefulBits, Imm, MSB, Depth);
2708 }
2709 
2710 static void getUsefulBitsFromOrWithShiftedReg(SDValue Op, APInt &UsefulBits,
2711  unsigned Depth) {
2712  uint64_t ShiftTypeAndValue =
2713  cast<const ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2).getNode())->getZExtValue();
2714  APInt Mask(UsefulBits);
2715  Mask.clearAllBits();
2716  Mask.flipAllBits();
2717 
2718  if (AArch64_AM::getShiftType(ShiftTypeAndValue) == AArch64_AM::LSL) {
2719  // Shift Left
2720  uint64_t ShiftAmt = AArch64_AM::getShiftValue(ShiftTypeAndValue);
2721  Mask <<= ShiftAmt;
2722  getUsefulBits(Op, Mask, Depth + 1);
2723  Mask.lshrInPlace(ShiftAmt);
2724  } else if (AArch64_AM::getShiftType(ShiftTypeAndValue) == AArch64_AM::LSR) {
2725  // Shift Right
2726  // We do not handle AArch64_AM::ASR, because the sign will change the
2727  // number of useful bits
2728  uint64_t ShiftAmt = AArch64_AM::getShiftValue(ShiftTypeAndValue);
2729  Mask.lshrInPlace(ShiftAmt);
2730  getUsefulBits(Op, Mask, Depth + 1);
2731  Mask <<= ShiftAmt;
2732  } else
2733  return;
2734 
2735  UsefulBits &= Mask;
2736 }
2737 
2738 static void getUsefulBitsFromBFM(SDValue Op, SDValue Orig, APInt &UsefulBits,
2739  unsigned Depth) {
2740  uint64_t Imm =
2741  cast<const ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2).getNode())->getZExtValue();
2742  uint64_t MSB =
2743  cast<const ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(3).getNode())->getZExtValue();
2744 
2745  APInt OpUsefulBits(UsefulBits);
2746  OpUsefulBits = 1;
2747 
2748  APInt ResultUsefulBits(UsefulBits.getBitWidth(), 0);
2749  ResultUsefulBits.flipAllBits();
2750  APInt Mask(UsefulBits.getBitWidth(), 0);
2751 
2752  getUsefulBits(Op, ResultUsefulBits, Depth + 1);
2753 
2754  if (MSB >= Imm) {
2755  // The instruction is a BFXIL.
2756  uint64_t Width = MSB - Imm + 1;
2757  uint64_t LSB = Imm;
2758 
2759  OpUsefulBits <<= Width;
2760  --OpUsefulBits;
2761 
2762  if (Op.getOperand(1) == Orig) {
2763  // Copy the low bits from the result to bits starting from LSB.
2764  Mask = ResultUsefulBits & OpUsefulBits;
2765  Mask <<= LSB;
2766  }
2767 
2768  if (Op.getOperand(0) == Orig)
2769  // Bits starting from LSB in the input contribute to the result.
2770  Mask |= (ResultUsefulBits & ~OpUsefulBits);
2771  } else {
2772  // The instruction is a BFI.
2773  uint64_t Width = MSB + 1;
2774  uint64_t LSB = UsefulBits.getBitWidth() - Imm;
2775 
2776  OpUsefulBits <<= Width;
2777  --OpUsefulBits;
2778  OpUsefulBits <<= LSB;
2779 
2780  if (Op.getOperand(1) == Orig) {
2781  // Copy the bits from the result to the zero bits.
2782  Mask = ResultUsefulBits & OpUsefulBits;
2783  Mask.lshrInPlace(LSB);
2784  }
2785 
2786  if (Op.getOperand(0) == Orig)
2787  Mask |= (ResultUsefulBits & ~OpUsefulBits);
2788  }
2789 
2790  UsefulBits &= Mask;
2791 }
2792 
2793 static void getUsefulBitsForUse(SDNode *UserNode, APInt &UsefulBits,
2794  SDValue Orig, unsigned Depth) {
2795 
2796  // Users of this node should have already been instruction selected
2797  // FIXME: Can we turn that into an assert?
2798  if (!UserNode->isMachineOpcode())
2799  return;
2800 
2801  switch (UserNode->getMachineOpcode()) {
2802  default:
2803  return;
2804  case AArch64::ANDSWri:
2805  case AArch64::ANDSXri:
2806  case AArch64::ANDWri:
2807  case AArch64::ANDXri:
2808  // We increment Depth only when we call the getUsefulBits
2809  return getUsefulBitsFromAndWithImmediate(SDValue(UserNode, 0), UsefulBits,
2810  Depth);
2811  case AArch64::UBFMWri:
2812  case AArch64::UBFMXri:
2813  return getUsefulBitsFromUBFM(SDValue(UserNode, 0), UsefulBits, Depth);
2814 
2815  case AArch64::ORRWrs:
2816  case AArch64::ORRXrs:
2817  if (UserNode->getOperand(0) != Orig && UserNode->getOperand(1) == Orig)
2818  getUsefulBitsFromOrWithShiftedReg(SDValue(UserNode, 0), UsefulBits,
2819  Depth);
2820  return;
2821  case AArch64::BFMWri:
2822  case AArch64::BFMXri:
2823  return getUsefulBitsFromBFM(SDValue(UserNode, 0), Orig, UsefulBits, Depth);
2824 
2825  case AArch64::STRBBui:
2826  case AArch64::STURBBi:
2827  if (UserNode->getOperand(0) != Orig)
2828  return;
2829  UsefulBits &= APInt(UsefulBits.getBitWidth(), 0xff);
2830  return;
2831 
2832  case AArch64::STRHHui:
2833  case AArch64::STURHHi:
2834  if (UserNode->getOperand(0) != Orig)
2835  return;
2836  UsefulBits &= APInt(UsefulBits.getBitWidth(), 0xffff);
2837  return;
2838  }
2839 }
2840 
2841 static void getUsefulBits(SDValue Op, APInt &UsefulBits, unsigned Depth) {
2842  if (Depth >= SelectionDAG::MaxRecursionDepth)
2843  return;
2844  // Initialize UsefulBits
2845  if (!Depth) {
2846  unsigned Bitwidth = Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
2847  // At the beginning, assume every produced bits is useful
2848  UsefulBits = APInt(Bitwidth, 0);
2849  UsefulBits.flipAllBits();
2850  }
2851  APInt UsersUsefulBits(UsefulBits.getBitWidth(), 0);
2852 
2853  for (SDNode *Node : Op.getNode()->uses()) {
2854  // A use cannot produce useful bits
2855  APInt UsefulBitsForUse = APInt(UsefulBits);
2856  getUsefulBitsForUse(Node, UsefulBitsForUse, Op, Depth);
2857  UsersUsefulBits |= UsefulBitsForUse;
2858  }
2859  // UsefulBits contains the produced bits that are meaningful for the
2860  // current definition, thus a user cannot make a bit meaningful at
2861  // this point
2862  UsefulBits &= UsersUsefulBits;
2863 }
2864 
2865 /// Create a machine node performing a notional SHL of Op by ShlAmount. If
2866 /// ShlAmount is negative, do a (logical) right-shift instead. If ShlAmount is
2867 /// 0, return Op unchanged.
2868 static SDValue getLeftShift(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDValue Op, int ShlAmount) {
2869  if (ShlAmount == 0)
2870  return Op;
2871 
2872  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
2873  SDLoc dl(Op);
2874  unsigned BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
2875  unsigned UBFMOpc = BitWidth == 32 ? AArch64::UBFMWri : AArch64::UBFMXri;
2876 
2877  SDNode *ShiftNode;
2878  if (ShlAmount > 0) {
2879  // LSL wD, wN, #Amt == UBFM wD, wN, #32-Amt, #31-Amt
2880  ShiftNode = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
2881  UBFMOpc, dl, VT, Op,
2882  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(BitWidth - ShlAmount, dl, VT),
2883  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(BitWidth - 1 - ShlAmount, dl, VT));
2884  } else {
2885  // LSR wD, wN, #Amt == UBFM wD, wN, #Amt, #32-1
2886  assert(ShlAmount < 0 && "expected right shift");
2887  int ShrAmount = -ShlAmount;
2888  ShiftNode = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
2889  UBFMOpc, dl, VT, Op, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ShrAmount, dl, VT),
2890  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(BitWidth - 1, dl, VT));
2891  }
2892 
2893  return SDValue(ShiftNode, 0);
2894 }
2895 
2896 // For bit-field-positioning pattern "(and (shl VAL, N), ShiftedMask)".
2897 static bool isBitfieldPositioningOpFromAnd(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDValue Op,
2898  bool BiggerPattern,
2899  const uint64_t NonZeroBits,
2900  SDValue &Src, int &DstLSB,
2901  int &Width);
2902 
2903 // For bit-field-positioning pattern "shl VAL, N)".
2904 static bool isBitfieldPositioningOpFromShl(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDValue Op,
2905  bool BiggerPattern,
2906  const uint64_t NonZeroBits,
2907  SDValue &Src, int &DstLSB,
2908  int &Width);
2909 
2910 /// Does this tree qualify as an attempt to move a bitfield into position,
2911 /// essentially "(and (shl VAL, N), Mask)" or (shl VAL, N).
2912 static bool isBitfieldPositioningOp(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDValue Op,
2913  bool BiggerPattern, SDValue &Src,
2914  int &DstLSB, int &Width) {
2915  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
2916  unsigned BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
2917  (void)BitWidth;
2918  assert(BitWidth == 32 || BitWidth == 64);
2919 
2920  KnownBits Known = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(Op);
2921 
2922  // Non-zero in the sense that they're not provably zero, which is the key
2923  // point if we want to use this value
2924  const uint64_t NonZeroBits = (~Known.Zero).getZExtValue();
2925  if (!isShiftedMask_64(NonZeroBits))
2926  return false;
2927 
2928  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
2929  default:
2930  break;
2931  case ISD::AND:
2932  return isBitfieldPositioningOpFromAnd(CurDAG, Op, BiggerPattern,
2933  NonZeroBits, Src, DstLSB, Width);
2934  case ISD::SHL:
2935  return isBitfieldPositioningOpFromShl(CurDAG, Op, BiggerPattern,
2936  NonZeroBits, Src, DstLSB, Width);
2937  }
2938 
2939  return false;
2940 }
2941 
2942 static bool isBitfieldPositioningOpFromAnd(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDValue Op,
2943  bool BiggerPattern,
2944  const uint64_t NonZeroBits,
2945  SDValue &Src, int &DstLSB,
2946  int &Width) {
2947  assert(isShiftedMask_64(NonZeroBits) && "Caller guaranteed");
2948 
2949  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
2950  assert((VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64) &&
2951  "Caller guarantees VT is one of i32 or i64");
2952  (void)VT;
2953 
2954  uint64_t AndImm;
2955  if (!isOpcWithIntImmediate(Op.getNode(), ISD::AND, AndImm))
2956  return false;
2957 
2958  // If (~AndImm & NonZeroBits) is not zero at POS, we know that
2959  // 1) (AndImm & (1 << POS) == 0)
2960  // 2) the result of AND is not zero at POS bit (according to NonZeroBits)
2961  //
2962  // 1) and 2) don't agree so something must be wrong (e.g., in
2963  // 'SelectionDAG::computeKnownBits')
2964  assert((~AndImm & NonZeroBits) == 0 &&
2965  "Something must be wrong (e.g., in SelectionDAG::computeKnownBits)");
2966 
2967  SDValue AndOp0 = Op.getOperand(0);
2968 
2969  uint64_t ShlImm;
2970  SDValue ShlOp0;
2971  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(AndOp0.getNode(), ISD::SHL, ShlImm)) {
2972  // For pattern "and(shl(val, N), shifted-mask)", 'ShlOp0' is set to 'val'.
2973  ShlOp0 = AndOp0.getOperand(0);
2974  } else if (VT == MVT::i64 && AndOp0.getOpcode() == ISD::ANY_EXTEND &&
2975  isOpcWithIntImmediate(AndOp0.getOperand(0).getNode(), ISD::SHL,
2976  ShlImm)) {
2977  // For pattern "and(any_extend(shl(val, N)), shifted-mask)"
2978 
2979  // ShlVal == shl(val, N), which is a left shift on a smaller type.
2980  SDValue ShlVal = AndOp0.getOperand(0);
2981 
2982  // Since this is after type legalization and ShlVal is extended to MVT::i64,
2983  // expect VT to be MVT::i32.
2984  assert((ShlVal.getValueType() == MVT::i32) && "Expect VT to be MVT::i32.");
2985 
2986  // Widens 'val' to MVT::i64 as the source of bit field positioning.
2987  ShlOp0 = Widen(CurDAG, ShlVal.getOperand(0));
2988  } else
2989  return false;
2990 
2991  // For !BiggerPattern, bail out if the AndOp0 has more than one use, since
2992  // then we'll end up generating AndOp0+UBFIZ instead of just keeping
2993  // AndOp0+AND.
2994  if (!BiggerPattern && !AndOp0.hasOneUse())
2995  return false;
2996 
2997  DstLSB = llvm::countr_zero(NonZeroBits);
2998  Width = llvm::countr_one(NonZeroBits >> DstLSB);
2999 
3000  // Bail out on large Width. This happens when no proper combining / constant
3001  // folding was performed.
3002  if (Width >= (int)VT.getSizeInBits()) {
3003  // If VT is i64, Width > 64 is insensible since NonZeroBits is uint64_t, and
3004  // Width == 64 indicates a missed dag-combine from "(and val, AllOnes)" to
3005  // "val".
3006  // If VT is i32, what Width >= 32 means:
3007  // - For "(and (any_extend(shl val, N)), shifted-mask)", the`and` Op
3008  // demands at least 'Width' bits (after dag-combiner). This together with
3009  // `any_extend` Op (undefined higher bits) indicates missed combination
3010  // when lowering the 'and' IR instruction to an machine IR instruction.
3011  LLVM_DEBUG(
3012  dbgs()
3013  << "Found large Width in bit-field-positioning -- this indicates no "
3014  "proper combining / constant folding was performed\n");
3015  return false;
3016  }
3017 
3018  // BFI encompasses sufficiently many nodes that it's worth inserting an extra
3019  // LSL/LSR if the mask in NonZeroBits doesn't quite match up with the ISD::SHL
3020  // amount. BiggerPattern is true when this pattern is being matched for BFI,
3021  // BiggerPattern is false when this pattern is being matched for UBFIZ, in
3022  // which case it is not profitable to insert an extra shift.
3023  if (ShlImm != uint64_t(DstLSB) && !BiggerPattern)
3024  return false;
3025 
3026  Src = getLeftShift(CurDAG, ShlOp0, ShlImm - DstLSB);
3027  return true;
3028 }
3029 
3030 // For node (shl (and val, mask), N)), returns true if the node is equivalent to
3031 // UBFIZ.
3032 static bool isSeveralBitsPositioningOpFromShl(const uint64_t ShlImm, SDValue Op,
3033  SDValue &Src, int &DstLSB,
3034  int &Width) {
3035  // Caller should have verified that N is a left shift with constant shift
3036  // amount; asserts that.
3037  assert(Op.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL &&
3038  "Op.getNode() should be a SHL node to call this function");
3039  assert(isIntImmediateEq(Op.getOperand(1), ShlImm) &&
3040  "Op.getNode() should shift ShlImm to call this function");
3041 
3042  uint64_t AndImm = 0;
3043  SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
3044  if (!isOpcWithIntImmediate(Op0.getNode(), ISD::AND, AndImm))
3045  return false;
3046 
3047  const uint64_t ShiftedAndImm = ((AndImm << ShlImm) >> ShlImm);
3048  if (isMask_64(ShiftedAndImm)) {
3049  // AndImm is a superset of (AllOnes >> ShlImm); in other words, AndImm
3050  // should end with Mask, and could be prefixed with random bits if those
3051  // bits are shifted out.
3052  //
3053  // For example, xyz11111 (with {x,y,z} being 0 or 1) is fine if ShlImm >= 3;
3054  // the AND result corresponding to those bits are shifted out, so it's fine
3055  // to not extract them.
3056  Width = llvm::countr_one(ShiftedAndImm);
3057  DstLSB = ShlImm;
3058  Src = Op0.getOperand(0);
3059  return true;
3060  }
3061  return false;
3062 }

3064 static bool isBitfieldPositioningOpFromShl(SelectionDAG *CurDAG, SDValue Op,
3065  bool BiggerPattern,
3066  const uint64_t NonZeroBits,
3067  SDValue &Src, int &DstLSB,
3068  int &Width) {
3069  assert(isShiftedMask_64(NonZeroBits) && "Caller guaranteed");
3070 
3071  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
3072  assert((VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64) &&
3073  "Caller guarantees that type is i32 or i64");
3074  (void)VT;
3075 
3076  uint64_t ShlImm;
3077  if (!isOpcWithIntImmediate(Op.getNode(), ISD::SHL, ShlImm))
3078  return false;
3079 
3080  if (!BiggerPattern && !Op.hasOneUse())
3081  return false;
3082 
3083  if (isSeveralBitsPositioningOpFromShl(ShlImm, Op, Src, DstLSB, Width))
3084  return true;
3085 
3086  DstLSB = llvm::countr_zero(NonZeroBits);
3087  Width = llvm::countr_one(NonZeroBits >> DstLSB);
3088 
3089  if (ShlImm != uint64_t(DstLSB) && !BiggerPattern)
3090  return false;
3091 
3092  Src = getLeftShift(CurDAG, Op.getOperand(0), ShlImm - DstLSB);
3093  return true;
3094 }

3096 static bool isShiftedMask(uint64_t Mask, EVT VT) {
3097  assert(VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64);
3098  if (VT == MVT::i32)
3099  return isShiftedMask_32(Mask);
3100  return isShiftedMask_64(Mask);
3101 }
3102 
3103 // Generate a BFI/BFXIL from 'or (and X, MaskImm), OrImm' iff the value being
3104 // inserted only sets known zero bits.
3105 static bool tryBitfieldInsertOpFromOrAndImm(SDNode *N, SelectionDAG *CurDAG) {
3106  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::OR && "Expect a OR operation");
3107 
3108  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3109  if (VT != MVT::i32 && VT != MVT::i64)
3110  return false;
3111 
3112  unsigned BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
3113 
3114  uint64_t OrImm;
3115  if (!isOpcWithIntImmediate(N, ISD::OR, OrImm))
3116  return false;
3117 
3118  // Skip this transformation if the ORR immediate can be encoded in the ORR.
3119  // Otherwise, we'll trade an AND+ORR for ORR+BFI/BFXIL, which is most likely
3120  // performance neutral.
3121  if (AArch64_AM::isLogicalImmediate(OrImm, BitWidth))
3122  return false;
3123 
3124  uint64_t MaskImm;
3125  SDValue And = N->getOperand(0);
3126  // Must be a single use AND with an immediate operand.
3127  if (!And.hasOneUse() ||
3128  !isOpcWithIntImmediate(And.getNode(), ISD::AND, MaskImm))
3129  return false;
3130 
3131  // Compute the Known Zero for the AND as this allows us to catch more general
3132  // cases than just looking for AND with imm.
3133  KnownBits Known = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(And);
3134 
3135  // Non-zero in the sense that they're not provably zero, which is the key
3136  // point if we want to use this value.
3137  uint64_t NotKnownZero = (~Known.Zero).getZExtValue();
3138 
3139  // The KnownZero mask must be a shifted mask (e.g., 1110..011, 11100..00).
3140  if (!isShiftedMask(Known.Zero.getZExtValue(), VT))
3141  return false;
3142 
3143  // The bits being inserted must only set those bits that are known to be zero.
3144  if ((OrImm & NotKnownZero) != 0) {
3145  // FIXME: It's okay if the OrImm sets NotKnownZero bits to 1, but we don't
3146  // currently handle this case.
3147  return false;
3148  }
3149 
3150  // BFI/BFXIL dst, src, #lsb, #width.
3151  int LSB = llvm::countr_one(NotKnownZero);
3152  int Width = BitWidth - APInt(BitWidth, NotKnownZero).countPopulation();
3153 
3154  // BFI/BFXIL is an alias of BFM, so translate to BFM operands.
3155  unsigned ImmR = (BitWidth - LSB) % BitWidth;
3156  unsigned ImmS = Width - 1;
3157 
3158  // If we're creating a BFI instruction avoid cases where we need more
3159  // instructions to materialize the BFI constant as compared to the original
3160  // ORR. A BFXIL will use the same constant as the original ORR, so the code
3161  // should be no worse in this case.
3162  bool IsBFI = LSB != 0;
3163  uint64_t BFIImm = OrImm >> LSB;
3164  if (IsBFI && !AArch64_AM::isLogicalImmediate(BFIImm, BitWidth)) {
3165  // We have a BFI instruction and we know the constant can't be materialized
3166  // with a ORR-immediate with the zero register.
3167  unsigned OrChunks = 0, BFIChunks = 0;
3168  for (unsigned Shift = 0; Shift < BitWidth; Shift += 16) {
3169  if (((OrImm >> Shift) & 0xFFFF) != 0)
3170  ++OrChunks;
3171  if (((BFIImm >> Shift) & 0xFFFF) != 0)
3172  ++BFIChunks;
3173  }
3174  if (BFIChunks > OrChunks)
3175  return false;
3176  }
3177 
3178  // Materialize the constant to be inserted.
3179  SDLoc DL(N);
3180  unsigned MOVIOpc = VT == MVT::i32 ? AArch64::MOVi32imm : AArch64::MOVi64imm;
3181  SDNode *MOVI = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
3182  MOVIOpc, DL, VT, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(BFIImm, DL, VT));
3183 
3184  // Create the BFI/BFXIL instruction.
3185  SDValue Ops[] = {And.getOperand(0), SDValue(MOVI, 0),
3186  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmR, DL, VT),
3187  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmS, DL, VT)};
3188  unsigned Opc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::BFMWri : AArch64::BFMXri;
3189  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, VT, Ops);
3190  return true;
3191 }
3192 
3193 static bool isWorthFoldingIntoOrrWithShift(SDValue Dst, SelectionDAG *CurDAG,
3194  SDValue &ShiftedOperand,
3195  uint64_t &EncodedShiftImm) {
3196  // Avoid folding Dst into ORR-with-shift if Dst has other uses than ORR.
3197  if (!Dst.hasOneUse())
3198  return false;
3199 
3200  EVT VT = Dst.getValueType();
3201  assert((VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64) &&
3202  "Caller should guarantee that VT is one of i32 or i64");
3203  const unsigned SizeInBits = VT.getSizeInBits();
3204 
3205  SDLoc DL(Dst.getNode());
3206  uint64_t AndImm, ShlImm;
3207  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(Dst.getNode(), ISD::AND, AndImm) &&
3208  isShiftedMask_64(AndImm)) {
3209  // Avoid transforming 'DstOp0' if it has other uses than the AND node.
3210  SDValue DstOp0 = Dst.getOperand(0);
3211  if (!DstOp0.hasOneUse())
3212  return false;
3213 
3214  // An example to illustrate the transformation
3215  // From:
3216  // lsr x8, x1, #1
3217  // and x8, x8, #0x3f80
3218  // bfxil x8, x1, #0, #7
3219  // To:
3220  // and x8, x23, #0x7f
3221  // ubfx x9, x23, #8, #7
3222  // orr x23, x8, x9, lsl #7
3223  //
3224  // The number of instructions remains the same, but ORR is faster than BFXIL
3225  // on many AArch64 processors (or as good as BFXIL if not faster). Besides,
3226  // the dependency chain is improved after the transformation.
3227  uint64_t SrlImm;
3228  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(DstOp0.getNode(), ISD::SRL, SrlImm)) {
3229  uint64_t NumTrailingZeroInShiftedMask = llvm::countr_zero(AndImm);
3230  if ((SrlImm + NumTrailingZeroInShiftedMask) < SizeInBits) {
3231  unsigned MaskWidth =
3232  llvm::countr_one(AndImm >> NumTrailingZeroInShiftedMask);
3233  unsigned UBFMOpc =
3234  (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::UBFMWri : AArch64::UBFMXri;
3235  SDNode *UBFMNode = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
3236  UBFMOpc, DL, VT, DstOp0.getOperand(0),
3237  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(SrlImm + NumTrailingZeroInShiftedMask, DL,
3238  VT),
3239  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(
3240  SrlImm + NumTrailingZeroInShiftedMask + MaskWidth - 1, DL, VT));
3241  ShiftedOperand = SDValue(UBFMNode, 0);
3242  EncodedShiftImm = AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(
3243  AArch64_AM::LSL, NumTrailingZeroInShiftedMask);
3244  return true;
3245  }
3246  }
3247  return false;
3248  }
3249 
3250  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(Dst.getNode(), ISD::SHL, ShlImm)) {
3251  ShiftedOperand = Dst.getOperand(0);
3252  EncodedShiftImm = AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSL, ShlImm);
3253  return true;
3254  }
3255 
3256  uint64_t SrlImm;
3257  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(Dst.getNode(), ISD::SRL, SrlImm)) {
3258  ShiftedOperand = Dst.getOperand(0);
3259  EncodedShiftImm = AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSR, SrlImm);
3260  return true;
3261  }
3262  return false;
3263 }
3264 
3265 // Given an 'ISD::OR' node that is going to be selected as BFM, analyze
3266 // the operands and select it to AArch64::ORR with shifted registers if
3267 // that's more efficient. Returns true iff selection to AArch64::ORR happens.
3268 static bool tryOrrWithShift(SDNode *N, SDValue OrOpd0, SDValue OrOpd1,
3269  SDValue Src, SDValue Dst, SelectionDAG *CurDAG,
3270  const bool BiggerPattern) {
3271  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3272  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::OR && "Expect N to be an OR node");
3273  assert(((N->getOperand(0) == OrOpd0 && N->getOperand(1) == OrOpd1) ||
3274  (N->getOperand(1) == OrOpd0 && N->getOperand(0) == OrOpd1)) &&
3275  "Expect OrOpd0 and OrOpd1 to be operands of ISD::OR");
3276  assert((VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64) &&
3277  "Expect result type to be i32 or i64 since N is combinable to BFM");
3278  SDLoc DL(N);
3279 
3280  // Bail out if BFM simplifies away one node in BFM Dst.
3281  if (OrOpd1 != Dst)
3282  return false;
3283 
3284  const unsigned OrrOpc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::ORRWrs : AArch64::ORRXrs;
3285  // For "BFM Rd, Rn, #immr, #imms", it's known that BFM simplifies away fewer
3286  // nodes from Rn (or inserts additional shift node) if BiggerPattern is true.
3287  if (BiggerPattern) {
3288  uint64_t SrcAndImm;
3289  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(OrOpd0.getNode(), ISD::AND, SrcAndImm) &&
3290  isMask_64(SrcAndImm) && OrOpd0.getOperand(0) == Src) {
3291  // OrOpd0 = AND Src, #Mask
3292  // So BFM simplifies away one AND node from Src and doesn't simplify away
3293  // nodes from Dst. If ORR with left-shifted operand also simplifies away
3294  // one node (from Rd), ORR is better since it has higher throughput and
3295  // smaller latency than BFM on many AArch64 processors (and for the rest
3296  // ORR is at least as good as BFM).
3297  SDValue ShiftedOperand;
3298  uint64_t EncodedShiftImm;
3299  if (isWorthFoldingIntoOrrWithShift(Dst, CurDAG, ShiftedOperand,
3300  EncodedShiftImm)) {
3301  SDValue Ops[] = {OrOpd0, ShiftedOperand,
3302  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(EncodedShiftImm, DL, VT)};
3303  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, OrrOpc, VT, Ops);
3304  return true;
3305  }
3306  }
3307  return false;
3308  }
3309 
3310  assert((!BiggerPattern) && "BiggerPattern should be handled above");
3311 
3312  uint64_t ShlImm;
3313  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(OrOpd0.getNode(), ISD::SHL, ShlImm)) {
3314  if (OrOpd0.getOperand(0) == Src && OrOpd0.hasOneUse()) {
3315  SDValue Ops[] = {
3316  Dst, Src,
3317  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(
3318  AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSL, ShlImm), DL, VT)};
3319  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, OrrOpc, VT, Ops);
3320  return true;
3321  }
3322 
3323  // Select the following pattern to left-shifted operand rather than BFI.
3324  // %val1 = op ..
3325  // %val2 = shl %val1, #imm
3326  // %res = or %val1, %val2
3327  //
3328  // If N is selected to be BFI, we know that
3329  // 1) OrOpd0 would be the operand from which extract bits (i.e., folded into
3330  // BFI) 2) OrOpd1 would be the destination operand (i.e., preserved)
3331  //
3332  // Instead of selecting N to BFI, fold OrOpd0 as a left shift directly.
3333  if (OrOpd0.getOperand(0) == OrOpd1) {
3334  SDValue Ops[] = {
3335  OrOpd1, OrOpd1,
3336  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(
3337  AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSL, ShlImm), DL, VT)};
3338  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, OrrOpc, VT, Ops);
3339  return true;
3340  }
3341  }
3342 
3343  uint64_t SrlImm;
3344  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(OrOpd0.getNode(), ISD::SRL, SrlImm)) {
3345  // Select the following pattern to right-shifted operand rather than BFXIL.
3346  // %val1 = op ..
3347  // %val2 = lshr %val1, #imm
3348  // %res = or %val1, %val2
3349  //
3350  // If N is selected to be BFXIL, we know that
3351  // 1) OrOpd0 would be the operand from which extract bits (i.e., folded into
3352  // BFXIL) 2) OrOpd1 would be the destination operand (i.e., preserved)
3353  //
3354  // Instead of selecting N to BFXIL, fold OrOpd0 as a right shift directly.
3355  if (OrOpd0.getOperand(0) == OrOpd1) {
3356  SDValue Ops[] = {
3357  OrOpd1, OrOpd1,
3358  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(
3359  AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSR, SrlImm), DL, VT)};
3360  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, OrrOpc, VT, Ops);
3361  return true;
3362  }
3363  }
3364 
3365  return false;
3366 }
3367 
3368 static bool tryBitfieldInsertOpFromOr(SDNode *N, const APInt &UsefulBits,
3369  SelectionDAG *CurDAG) {
3370  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::OR && "Expect a OR operation");
3371 
3372  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3373  if (VT != MVT::i32 && VT != MVT::i64)
3374  return false;
3375 
3376  unsigned BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
3377 
3378  // Because of simplify-demanded-bits in DAGCombine, involved masks may not
3379  // have the expected shape. Try to undo that.
3380 
3381  unsigned NumberOfIgnoredLowBits = UsefulBits.countTrailingZeros();
3382  unsigned NumberOfIgnoredHighBits = UsefulBits.countLeadingZeros();
3383 
3384  // Given a OR operation, check if we have the following pattern
3385  // ubfm c, b, imm, imm2 (or something that does the same jobs, see
3386  // isBitfieldExtractOp)
3387  // d = e & mask2 ; where mask is a binary sequence of 1..10..0 and
3388  // countTrailingZeros(mask2) == imm2 - imm + 1
3389  // f = d | c
3390  // if yes, replace the OR instruction with:
3391  // f = BFM Opd0, Opd1, LSB, MSB ; where LSB = imm, and MSB = imm2
3392 
3393  // OR is commutative, check all combinations of operand order and values of
3394  // BiggerPattern, i.e.
3395  // Opd0, Opd1, BiggerPattern=false
3396  // Opd1, Opd0, BiggerPattern=false
3397  // Opd0, Opd1, BiggerPattern=true
3398  // Opd1, Opd0, BiggerPattern=true
3399  // Several of these combinations may match, so check with BiggerPattern=false
3400  // first since that will produce better results by matching more instructions
3401  // and/or inserting fewer extra instructions.
3402  for (int I = 0; I < 4; ++I) {
3403 
3404  SDValue Dst, Src;
3405  unsigned ImmR, ImmS;
3406  bool BiggerPattern = I / 2;
3407  SDValue OrOpd0Val = N->getOperand(I % 2);
3408  SDNode *OrOpd0 = OrOpd0Val.getNode();
3409  SDValue OrOpd1Val = N->getOperand((I + 1) % 2);
3410  SDNode *OrOpd1 = OrOpd1Val.getNode();
3411 
3412  unsigned BFXOpc;
3413  int DstLSB, Width;
3414  if (isBitfieldExtractOp(CurDAG, OrOpd0, BFXOpc, Src, ImmR, ImmS,
3415  NumberOfIgnoredLowBits, BiggerPattern)) {
3416  // Check that the returned opcode is compatible with the pattern,
3417  // i.e., same type and zero extended (U and not S)
3418  if ((BFXOpc != AArch64::UBFMXri && VT == MVT::i64) ||
3419  (BFXOpc != AArch64::UBFMWri && VT == MVT::i32))
3420  continue;
3421 
3422  // Compute the width of the bitfield insertion
3423  DstLSB = 0;
3424  Width = ImmS - ImmR + 1;
3425  // FIXME: This constraint is to catch bitfield insertion we may
3426  // want to widen the pattern if we want to grab general bitfied
3427  // move case
3428  if (Width <= 0)
3429  continue;
3430 
3431  // If the mask on the insertee is correct, we have a BFXIL operation. We
3432  // can share the ImmR and ImmS values from the already-computed UBFM.
3433  } else if (isBitfieldPositioningOp(CurDAG, OrOpd0Val,
3434  BiggerPattern,
3435  Src, DstLSB, Width)) {
3436  ImmR = (BitWidth - DstLSB) % BitWidth;
3437  ImmS = Width - 1;
3438  } else
3439  continue;
3440 
3441  // Check the second part of the pattern
3442  EVT VT = OrOpd1Val.getValueType();
3443  assert((VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::i64) && "unexpected OR operand");
3444 
3445  // Compute the Known Zero for the candidate of the first operand.
3446  // This allows to catch more general case than just looking for
3447  // AND with imm. Indeed, simplify-demanded-bits may have removed
3448  // the AND instruction because it proves it was useless.
3449  KnownBits Known = CurDAG->computeKnownBits(OrOpd1Val);
3450 
3451  // Check if there is enough room for the second operand to appear
3452  // in the first one
3453  APInt BitsToBeInserted =
3454  APInt::getBitsSet(Known.getBitWidth(), DstLSB, DstLSB + Width);
3455 
3456  if ((BitsToBeInserted & ~Known.Zero) != 0)
3457  continue;
3458 
3459  // Set the first operand
3460  uint64_t Imm;
3461  if (isOpcWithIntImmediate(OrOpd1, ISD::AND, Imm) &&
3462  isBitfieldDstMask(Imm, BitsToBeInserted, NumberOfIgnoredHighBits, VT))
3463  // In that case, we can eliminate the AND
3464  Dst = OrOpd1->getOperand(0);
3465  else
3466  // Maybe the AND has been removed by simplify-demanded-bits
3467  // or is useful because it discards more bits
3468  Dst = OrOpd1Val;
3469 
3470  // Before selecting ISD::OR node to AArch64::BFM, see if an AArch64::ORR
3471  // with shifted operand is more efficient.
3472  if (tryOrrWithShift(N, OrOpd0Val, OrOpd1Val, Src, Dst, CurDAG,
3473  BiggerPattern))
3474  return true;
3475 
3476  // both parts match
3477  SDLoc DL(N);
3478  SDValue Ops[] = {Dst, Src, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmR, DL, VT),
3479  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmS, DL, VT)};
3480  unsigned Opc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::BFMWri : AArch64::BFMXri;
3481  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, VT, Ops);
3482  return true;
3483  }
3484 
3485  // Generate a BFXIL from 'or (and X, Mask0Imm), (and Y, Mask1Imm)' iff
3486  // Mask0Imm and ~Mask1Imm are equivalent and one of the MaskImms is a shifted
3487  // mask (e.g., 0x000ffff0).
3488  uint64_t Mask0Imm, Mask1Imm;
3489  SDValue And0 = N->getOperand(0);
3490  SDValue And1 = N->getOperand(1);
3491  if (And0.hasOneUse() && And1.hasOneUse() &&
3492  isOpcWithIntImmediate(And0.getNode(), ISD::AND, Mask0Imm) &&
3493  isOpcWithIntImmediate(And1.getNode(), ISD::AND, Mask1Imm) &&
3494  APInt(BitWidth, Mask0Imm) == ~APInt(BitWidth, Mask1Imm) &&
3495  (isShiftedMask(Mask0Imm, VT) || isShiftedMask(Mask1Imm, VT))) {
3496 
3497  // ORR is commutative, so canonicalize to the form 'or (and X, Mask0Imm),
3498  // (and Y, Mask1Imm)' where Mask1Imm is the shifted mask masking off the
3499  // bits to be inserted.
3500  if (isShiftedMask(Mask0Imm, VT)) {
3501  std::swap(And0, And1);
3502  std::swap(Mask0Imm, Mask1Imm);
3503  }
3504 
3505  SDValue Src = And1->getOperand(0);
3506  SDValue Dst = And0->getOperand(0);
3507  unsigned LSB = llvm::countr_zero(Mask1Imm);
3508  int Width = BitWidth - APInt(BitWidth, Mask0Imm).countPopulation();
3509 
3510  // The BFXIL inserts the low-order bits from a source register, so right
3511  // shift the needed bits into place.
3512  SDLoc DL(N);
3513  unsigned ShiftOpc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::UBFMWri : AArch64::UBFMXri;
3514  uint64_t LsrImm = LSB;
3515  if (Src->hasOneUse() &&
3516  isOpcWithIntImmediate(Src.getNode(), ISD::SRL, LsrImm) &&
3517  (LsrImm + LSB) < BitWidth) {
3518  Src = Src->getOperand(0);
3519  LsrImm += LSB;
3520  }
3521 
3522  SDNode *LSR = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
3523  ShiftOpc, DL, VT, Src, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(LsrImm, DL, VT),
3524  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(BitWidth - 1, DL, VT));
3525 
3526  // BFXIL is an alias of BFM, so translate to BFM operands.
3527  unsigned ImmR = (BitWidth - LSB) % BitWidth;
3528  unsigned ImmS = Width - 1;
3529 
3530  // Create the BFXIL instruction.
3531  SDValue Ops[] = {Dst, SDValue(LSR, 0),
3532  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmR, DL, VT),
3533  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmS, DL, VT)};
3534  unsigned Opc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::BFMWri : AArch64::BFMXri;
3535  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, VT, Ops);
3536  return true;
3537  }
3538 
3539  return false;
3540 }
3541 
3542 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryBitfieldInsertOp(SDNode *N) {
3543  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::OR)
3544  return false;
3545 
3546  APInt NUsefulBits;
3547  getUsefulBits(SDValue(N, 0), NUsefulBits);
3548 
3549  // If all bits are not useful, just return UNDEF.
3550  if (!NUsefulBits) {
3551  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF, N->getValueType(0));
3552  return true;
3553  }
3554 
3555  if (tryBitfieldInsertOpFromOr(N, NUsefulBits, CurDAG))
3556  return true;
3557 
3558  return tryBitfieldInsertOpFromOrAndImm(N, CurDAG);
3559 }
3560 
3561 /// SelectBitfieldInsertInZeroOp - Match a UBFIZ instruction that is the
3562 /// equivalent of a left shift by a constant amount followed by an and masking
3563 /// out a contiguous set of bits.
3564 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryBitfieldInsertInZeroOp(SDNode *N) {
3565  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::AND)
3566  return false;
3567 
3568  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3569  if (VT != MVT::i32 && VT != MVT::i64)
3570  return false;
3571 
3572  SDValue Op0;
3573  int DstLSB, Width;
3574  if (!isBitfieldPositioningOp(CurDAG, SDValue(N, 0), /*BiggerPattern=*/false,
3575  Op0, DstLSB, Width))
3576  return false;
3577 
3578  // ImmR is the rotate right amount.
3579  unsigned ImmR = (VT.getSizeInBits() - DstLSB) % VT.getSizeInBits();
3580  // ImmS is the most significant bit of the source to be moved.
3581  unsigned ImmS = Width - 1;
3582 
3583  SDLoc DL(N);
3584  SDValue Ops[] = {Op0, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmR, DL, VT),
3585  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmS, DL, VT)};
3586  unsigned Opc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::UBFMWri : AArch64::UBFMXri;
3587  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, VT, Ops);
3588  return true;
3589 }
3590 
3591 /// tryShiftAmountMod - Take advantage of built-in mod of shift amount in
3592 /// variable shift/rotate instructions.
3593 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryShiftAmountMod(SDNode *N) {
3594  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
3595 
3596  unsigned Opc;
3597  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
3598  case ISD::ROTR:
3599  Opc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::RORVWr : AArch64::RORVXr;
3600  break;
3601  case ISD::SHL:
3602  Opc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::LSLVWr : AArch64::LSLVXr;
3603  break;
3604  case ISD::SRL:
3605  Opc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::LSRVWr : AArch64::LSRVXr;
3606  break;
3607  case ISD::SRA:
3608  Opc = (VT == MVT::i32) ? AArch64::ASRVWr : AArch64::ASRVXr;
3609  break;
3610  default:
3611  return false;
3612  }
3613 
3614  uint64_t Size;
3615  uint64_t Bits;
3616  if (VT == MVT::i32) {
3617  Bits = 5;
3618  Size = 32;
3619  } else if (VT == MVT::i64) {
3620  Bits = 6;
3621  Size = 64;
3622  } else
3623  return false;
3624 
3625  SDValue ShiftAmt = N->getOperand(1);
3626  SDLoc DL(N);
3627  SDValue NewShiftAmt;
3628 
3629  // Skip over an extend of the shift amount.
3630  if (ShiftAmt->getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND ||
3631  ShiftAmt->getOpcode() == ISD::ANY_EXTEND)
3632  ShiftAmt = ShiftAmt->getOperand(0);
3633 
3634  if (ShiftAmt->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD || ShiftAmt->getOpcode() == ISD::SUB) {
3635  SDValue Add0 = ShiftAmt->getOperand(0);
3636  SDValue Add1 = ShiftAmt->getOperand(1);
3637  uint64_t Add0Imm;
3638  uint64_t Add1Imm;
3639  if (isIntImmediate(Add1, Add1Imm) && (Add1Imm % Size == 0)) {
3640  // If we are shifting by X+/-N where N == 0 mod Size, then just shift by X
3641  // to avoid the ADD/SUB.
3642  NewShiftAmt = Add0;
3643  } else if (ShiftAmt->getOpcode() == ISD::SUB &&
3644  isIntImmediate(Add0, Add0Imm) && Add0Imm != 0 &&
3645  (Add0Imm % Size == 0)) {
3646  // If we are shifting by N-X where N == 0 mod Size, then just shift by -X
3647  // to generate a NEG instead of a SUB from a constant.
3648  unsigned NegOpc;
3649  unsigned ZeroReg;
3650  EVT SubVT = ShiftAmt->getValueType(0);
3651  if (SubVT == MVT::i32) {
3652  NegOpc = AArch64::SUBWrr;
3653  ZeroReg = AArch64::WZR;
3654  } else {
3655  assert(SubVT == MVT::i64);
3656  NegOpc = AArch64::SUBXrr;
3657  ZeroReg = AArch64::XZR;
3658  }
3659  SDValue Zero =
3660  CurDAG->getCopyFromReg(CurDAG->getEntryNode(), DL, ZeroReg, SubVT);
3661  MachineSDNode *Neg =
3662  CurDAG->getMachineNode(NegOpc, DL, SubVT, Zero, Add1);
3663  NewShiftAmt = SDValue(Neg, 0);
3664  } else if (ShiftAmt->getOpcode() == ISD::SUB &&
3665  isIntImmediate(Add0, Add0Imm) && (Add0Imm % Size == Size - 1)) {
3666  // If we are shifting by N-X where N == -1 mod Size, then just shift by ~X
3667  // to generate a NOT instead of a SUB from a constant.
3668  unsigned NotOpc;
3669  unsigned ZeroReg;
3670  EVT SubVT = ShiftAmt->getValueType(0);
3671  if (SubVT == MVT::i32) {
3672  NotOpc = AArch64::ORNWrr;
3673  ZeroReg = AArch64::WZR;
3674  } else {
3675  assert(SubVT == MVT::i64);
3676  NotOpc = AArch64::ORNXrr;
3677  ZeroReg = AArch64::XZR;
3678  }
3679  SDValue Zero =
3680  CurDAG->getCopyFromReg(CurDAG->getEntryNode(), DL, ZeroReg, SubVT);
3681  MachineSDNode *Not =
3682  CurDAG->getMachineNode(NotOpc, DL, SubVT, Zero, Add1);
3683  NewShiftAmt = SDValue(Not, 0);
3684  } else
3685  return false;
3686  } else {
3687  // If the shift amount is masked with an AND, check that the mask covers the
3688  // bits that are implicitly ANDed off by the above opcodes and if so, skip
3689  // the AND.
3690  uint64_t MaskImm;
3691  if (!isOpcWithIntImmediate(ShiftAmt.getNode(), ISD::AND, MaskImm) &&
3692  !isOpcWithIntImmediate(ShiftAmt.getNode(), AArch64ISD::ANDS, MaskImm))
3693  return false;
3694 
3695  if ((unsigned)llvm::countr_one(MaskImm) < Bits)
3696  return false;
3697 
3698  NewShiftAmt = ShiftAmt->getOperand(0);
3699  }
3700 
3701  // Narrow/widen the shift amount to match the size of the shift operation.
3702  if (VT == MVT::i32)
3703  NewShiftAmt = narrowIfNeeded(CurDAG, NewShiftAmt);
3704  else if (VT == MVT::i64 && NewShiftAmt->getValueType(0) == MVT::i32) {
3705  SDValue SubReg = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::sub_32, DL, MVT::i32);
3706  MachineSDNode *Ext = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
3707  AArch64::SUBREG_TO_REG, DL, VT,
3708  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i64), NewShiftAmt, SubReg);
3709  NewShiftAmt = SDValue(Ext, 0);
3710  }
3711 
3712  SDValue Ops[] = {N->getOperand(0), NewShiftAmt};
3713  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opc, VT, Ops);
3714  return true;
3715 }
3716 
3717 bool
3718 AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectCVTFixedPosOperand(SDValue N, SDValue &FixedPos,
3719  unsigned RegWidth) {
3720  APFloat FVal(0.0);
3721  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N))
3722  FVal = CN->getValueAPF();
3723  else if (LoadSDNode *LN = dyn_cast<LoadSDNode>(N)) {
3724  // Some otherwise illegal constants are allowed in this case.
3725  if (LN->getOperand(1).getOpcode() != AArch64ISD::ADDlow ||
3726  !isa<ConstantPoolSDNode>(LN->getOperand(1)->getOperand(1)))
3727  return false;
3728 
3729  ConstantPoolSDNode *CN =
3730  dyn_cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(LN->getOperand(1)->getOperand(1));
3731  FVal = cast<ConstantFP>(CN->getConstVal())->getValueAPF();
3732  } else
3733  return false;
3734 
3735  // An FCVT[SU] instruction performs: convertToInt(Val * 2^fbits) where fbits
3736  // is between 1 and 32 for a destination w-register, or 1 and 64 for an
3737  // x-register.
3738  //
3739  // By this stage, we've detected (fp_to_[su]int (fmul Val, THIS_NODE)) so we
3740  // want THIS_NODE to be 2^fbits. This is much easier to deal with using
3741  // integers.
3742  bool IsExact;
3743 
3744  // fbits is between 1 and 64 in the worst-case, which means the fmul
3745  // could have 2^64 as an actual operand. Need 65 bits of precision.
3746  APSInt IntVal(65, true);
3747  FVal.convertToInteger(IntVal, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &IsExact);
3748 
3749  // N.b. isPowerOf2 also checks for > 0.
3750  if (!IsExact || !IntVal.isPowerOf2()) return false;
3751  unsigned FBits = IntVal.logBase2();
3752 
3753  // Checks above should have guaranteed that we haven't lost information in
3754  // finding FBits, but it must still be in range.
3755  if (FBits == 0 || FBits > RegWidth) return false;
3756 
3757  FixedPos = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(FBits, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
3758  return true;
3759 }
3760 
3761 // Inspects a register string of the form o0:op1:CRn:CRm:op2 gets the fields
3762 // of the string and obtains the integer values from them and combines these
3763 // into a single value to be used in the MRS/MSR instruction.
3764 static int getIntOperandFromRegisterString(StringRef RegString) {
3765  SmallVector<StringRef, 5> Fields;
3766  RegString.split(Fields, ':');
3767 
3768  if (Fields.size() == 1)
3769  return -1;
3770 
3771  assert(Fields.size() == 5
3772  && "Invalid number of fields in read register string");
3773 
3774  SmallVector<int, 5> Ops;
3775  bool AllIntFields = true;
3776 
3777  for (StringRef Field : Fields) {
3778  unsigned IntField;
3779  AllIntFields &= !Field.getAsInteger(10, IntField);
3780  Ops.push_back(IntField);
3781  }
3782 
3783  assert(AllIntFields &&
3784  "Unexpected non-integer value in special register string.");
3785  (void)AllIntFields;
3786 
3787  // Need to combine the integer fields of the string into a single value
3788  // based on the bit encoding of MRS/MSR instruction.
3789  return (Ops[0] << 14) | (Ops[1] << 11) | (Ops[2] << 7) |
3790  (Ops[3] << 3) | (Ops[4]);
3791 }
3792 
3793 // Lower the read_register intrinsic to an MRS instruction node if the special
3794 // register string argument is either of the form detailed in the ALCE (the
3795 // form described in getIntOperandsFromRegsterString) or is a named register
3796 // known by the MRS SysReg mapper.
3797 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryReadRegister(SDNode *N) {
3798  const auto *MD = cast<MDNodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
3799  const auto *RegString = cast<MDString>(MD->getMD()->getOperand(0));
3800  SDLoc DL(N);
3801 
3802  bool ReadIs128Bit = N->getOpcode() == AArch64ISD::MRRS;
3803 
3804  unsigned Opcode64Bit = AArch64::MRS;
3805  int Imm = getIntOperandFromRegisterString(RegString->getString());
3806  if (Imm == -1) {
3807  // No match, Use the sysreg mapper to map the remaining possible strings to
3808  // the value for the register to be used for the instruction operand.
3809  const auto *TheReg =
3810  AArch64SysReg::lookupSysRegByName(RegString->getString());
3811  if (TheReg && TheReg->Readable &&
3812  TheReg->haveFeatures(Subtarget->getFeatureBits()))
3813  Imm = TheReg->Encoding;
3814  else
3815  Imm = AArch64SysReg::parseGenericRegister(RegString->getString());
3816 
3817  if (Imm == -1) {
3818  // Still no match, see if this is "pc" or give up.
3819  if (!ReadIs128Bit && RegString->getString() == "pc") {
3820  Opcode64Bit = AArch64::ADR;
3821  Imm = 0;
3822  } else {
3823  return false;
3824  }
3825  }
3826  }
3827 
3828  SDValue InChain = N->getOperand(0);
3829  SDValue SysRegImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Imm, DL, MVT::i32);
3830  if (!ReadIs128Bit) {
3831  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, Opcode64Bit, MVT::i64, MVT::Other /* Chain */,
3832  {SysRegImm, InChain});
3833  } else {
3834  SDNode *MRRS = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
3835  AArch64::MRRS, DL,
3836  {MVT::Untyped /* XSeqPair */, MVT::Other /* Chain */},
3837  {SysRegImm, InChain});
3838 
3839  // Sysregs are not endian. The even register always contains the low half
3840  // of the register.
3841  SDValue Lo = CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(AArch64::sube64, DL, MVT::i64,
3842  SDValue(MRRS, 0));
3843  SDValue Hi = CurDAG->getTargetExtractSubreg(AArch64::subo64, DL, MVT::i64,
3844  SDValue(MRRS, 0));
3845  SDValue OutChain = SDValue(MRRS, 1);
3846 
3847  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 0), Lo);
3848  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 1), Hi);
3849  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 2), OutChain);
3850  };
3851  return true;
3852 }
3853 
3854 // Lower the write_register intrinsic to an MSR instruction node if the special
3855 // register string argument is either of the form detailed in the ALCE (the
3856 // form described in getIntOperandsFromRegsterString) or is a named register
3857 // known by the MSR SysReg mapper.
3858 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::tryWriteRegister(SDNode *N) {
3859  const auto *MD = cast<MDNodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
3860  const auto *RegString = cast<MDString>(MD->getMD()->getOperand(0));
3861  SDLoc DL(N);
3862 
3863  bool WriteIs128Bit = N->getOpcode() == AArch64ISD::MSRR;
3864 
3865  if (!WriteIs128Bit) {
3866  // Check if the register was one of those allowed as the pstatefield value
3867  // in the MSR (immediate) instruction. To accept the values allowed in the
3868  // pstatefield for the MSR (immediate) instruction, we also require that an
3869  // immediate value has been provided as an argument, we know that this is
3870  // the case as it has been ensured by semantic checking.
3871  auto trySelectPState = [&](auto PMapper, unsigned State) {
3872  if (PMapper) {
3873  assert(isa<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(2)) &&
3874  "Expected a constant integer expression.");
3875  unsigned Reg = PMapper->Encoding;
3876  uint64_t Immed = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(2))->getZExtValue();
3877  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(
3878  N, State, MVT::Other, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Reg, DL, MVT::i32),
3879  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Immed, DL, MVT::i16), N->getOperand(0));
3880  return true;
3881  }
3882  return false;
3883  };
3884 
3885  if (trySelectPState(
3886  AArch64PState::lookupPStateImm0_15ByName(RegString->getString()),
3887  AArch64::MSRpstateImm4))
3888  return true;
3889  if (trySelectPState(
3890  AArch64PState::lookupPStateImm0_1ByName(RegString->getString()),
3891  AArch64::MSRpstateImm1))
3892  return true;
3893  }
3894 
3895  int Imm = getIntOperandFromRegisterString(RegString->getString());
3896  if (Imm == -1) {
3897  // Use the sysreg mapper to attempt to map the remaining possible strings
3898  // to the value for the register to be used for the MSR (register)
3899  // instruction operand.
3900  auto TheReg = AArch64SysReg::lookupSysRegByName(RegString->getString());
3901  if (TheReg && TheReg->Writeable &&
3902  TheReg->haveFeatures(Subtarget->getFeatureBits()))
3903  Imm = TheReg->Encoding;
3904  else
3905  Imm = AArch64SysReg::parseGenericRegister(RegString->getString());
3906 
3907  if (Imm == -1)
3908  return false;
3909  }
3910 
3911  SDValue InChain = N->getOperand(0);
3912  if (!WriteIs128Bit) {
3913  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, AArch64::MSR, MVT::Other,
3914  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Imm, DL, MVT::i32),
3915  N->getOperand(2), InChain);
3916  } else {
3917  // No endian swap. The lower half always goes into the even subreg, and the
3918  // higher half always into the odd supreg.
3919  SDNode *Pair = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
3920  TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, MVT::Untyped /* XSeqPair */,
3921  {CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::XSeqPairsClassRegClass.getID(), DL,
3922  MVT::i32),
3923  N->getOperand(2),
3924  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::sube64, DL, MVT::i32),
3925  N->getOperand(3),
3926  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::subo64, DL, MVT::i32)});
3927 
3928  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(N, AArch64::MSRR, MVT::Other,
3929  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Imm, DL, MVT::i32),
3930  SDValue(Pair, 0), InChain);
3931  }
3932 
3933  return true;
3934 }
3935 
3936 /// We've got special pseudo-instructions for these
3937 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectCMP_SWAP(SDNode *N) {
3938  unsigned Opcode;
3939  EVT MemTy = cast<MemSDNode>(N)->getMemoryVT();
3940 
3941  // Leave IR for LSE if subtarget supports it.
3942  if (Subtarget->hasLSE()) return false;
3943 
3944  if (MemTy == MVT::i8)
3945  Opcode = AArch64::CMP_SWAP_8;
3946  else if (MemTy == MVT::i16)
3947  Opcode = AArch64::CMP_SWAP_16;
3948  else if (MemTy == MVT::i32)
3949  Opcode = AArch64::CMP_SWAP_32;
3950  else if (MemTy == MVT::i64)
3951  Opcode = AArch64::CMP_SWAP_64;
3952  else
3953  llvm_unreachable("Unknown AtomicCmpSwap type");
3954 
3955  MVT RegTy = MemTy == MVT::i64 ? MVT::i64 : MVT::i32;
3956  SDValue Ops[] = {N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2), N->getOperand(3),
3957  N->getOperand(0)};
3958  SDNode *CmpSwap = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
3959  Opcode, SDLoc(N),
3960  CurDAG->getVTList(RegTy, MVT::i32, MVT::Other), Ops);
3961 
3962  MachineMemOperand *MemOp = cast<MemSDNode>(N)->getMemOperand();
3963  CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast<MachineSDNode>(CmpSwap), {MemOp});
3964 
3965  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 0), SDValue(CmpSwap, 0));
3966  ReplaceUses(SDValue(N, 1), SDValue(CmpSwap, 2));
3967  CurDAG->RemoveDeadNode(N);
3968 
3969  return true;
3970 }
3971 
3972 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectSVEAddSubImm(SDValue N, MVT VT, SDValue &Imm,
3973  SDValue &Shift) {
3974  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(N))
3975  return false;
3976 
3977  SDLoc DL(N);
3978  uint64_t Val = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)
3979  ->getAPIntValue()
3980  .trunc(VT.getFixedSizeInBits())
3981  .getZExtValue();
3982 
3983  switch (VT.SimpleTy) {
3984  case MVT::i8:
3985  // All immediates are supported.
3986  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
3987  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val, DL, MVT::i32);
3988  return true;
3989  case MVT::i16:
3990  case MVT::i32:
3991  case MVT::i64:
3992  // Support 8bit unsigned immediates.
3993  if (Val <= 255) {
3994  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
3995  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val, DL, MVT::i32);
3996  return true;
3997  }
3998  // Support 16bit unsigned immediates that are a multiple of 256.
3999  if (Val <= 65280 && Val % 256 == 0) {
4000  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(8, DL, MVT::i32);
4001  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val >> 8, DL, MVT::i32);
4002  return true;
4003  }
4004  break;
4005  default:
4006  break;
4007  }
4008 
4009  return false;
4010 }
4011 
4012 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectSVECpyDupImm(SDValue N, MVT VT, SDValue &Imm,
4013  SDValue &Shift) {
4014  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(N))
4015  return false;
4016 
4017  SDLoc DL(N);
4018  int64_t Val = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)
4019  ->getAPIntValue()
4020  .trunc(VT.getFixedSizeInBits())
4021  .getSExtValue();
4022 
4023  switch (VT.SimpleTy) {
4024  case MVT::i8:
4025  // All immediates are supported.
4026  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
4027  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val & 0xFF, DL, MVT::i32);
4028  return true;
4029  case MVT::i16:
4030  case MVT::i32:
4031  case MVT::i64:
4032  // Support 8bit signed immediates.
4033  if (Val >= -128 && Val <= 127) {
4034  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
4035  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Val & 0xFF, DL, MVT::i32);
4036  return true;
4037  }
4038  // Support 16bit signed immediates that are a multiple of 256.
4039  if (Val >= -32768 && Val <= 32512 && Val % 256 == 0) {
4040  Shift = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(8, DL, MVT::i32);
4041  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant((Val >> 8) & 0xFF, DL, MVT::i32);
4042  return true;
4043  }
4044  break;
4045  default:
4046  break;
4047  }
4048 
4049  return false;
4050 }

4052 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectSVESignedArithImm(SDValue N, SDValue &Imm) {
4053  if (auto CNode = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)) {
4054  int64_t ImmVal = CNode->getSExtValue();
4055  SDLoc DL(N);
4056  if (ImmVal >= -128 && ImmVal < 128) {
4057  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmVal, DL, MVT::i32);
4058  return true;
4059  }
4060  }
4061  return false;
4062 }
4063 
4064 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectSVEArithImm(SDValue N, MVT VT, SDValue &Imm) {
4065  if (auto CNode = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)) {
4066  uint64_t ImmVal = CNode->getZExtValue();
4067 
4068  switch (VT.SimpleTy) {
4069  case MVT::i8:
4070  ImmVal &= 0xFF;
4071  break;
4072  case MVT::i16:
4073  ImmVal &= 0xFFFF;
4074  break;
4075  case MVT::i32:
4076  ImmVal &= 0xFFFFFFFF;
4077  break;
4078  case MVT::i64:
4079  break;
4080  default:
4081  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected type");
4082  }
4083 
4084  if (ImmVal < 256) {
4085  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmVal, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
4086  return true;
4087  }
4088  }
4089  return false;
4090 }

4092 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectSVELogicalImm(SDValue N, MVT VT, SDValue &Imm,
4093  bool Invert) {
4094  if (auto CNode = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)) {
4095  uint64_t ImmVal = CNode->getZExtValue();
4096  SDLoc DL(N);
4097 
4098  if (Invert)
4099  ImmVal = ~ImmVal;
4100 
4101  // Shift mask depending on type size.
4102  switch (VT.SimpleTy) {
4103  case MVT::i8:
4104  ImmVal &= 0xFF;
4105  ImmVal |= ImmVal << 8;
4106  ImmVal |= ImmVal << 16;
4107  ImmVal |= ImmVal << 32;
4108  break;
4109  case MVT::i16:
4110  ImmVal &= 0xFFFF;
4111  ImmVal |= ImmVal << 16;
4112  ImmVal |= ImmVal << 32;
4113  break;
4114  case MVT::i32:
4115  ImmVal &= 0xFFFFFFFF;
4116  ImmVal |= ImmVal << 32;
4117  break;
4118  case MVT::i64:
4119  break;
4120  default:
4121  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected type");
4122  }
4123 
4124  uint64_t encoding;
4125  if (AArch64_AM::processLogicalImmediate(ImmVal, 64, encoding)) {
4126  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(encoding, DL, MVT::i64);
4127  return true;
4128  }
4129  }
4130  return false;
4131 }
4132 
4133 // SVE shift intrinsics allow shift amounts larger than the element's bitwidth.
4134 // Rather than attempt to normalise everything we can sometimes saturate the
4135 // shift amount during selection. This function also allows for consistent
4136 // isel patterns by ensuring the resulting "Imm" node is of the i32 type
4137 // required by the instructions.
4138 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectSVEShiftImm(SDValue N, uint64_t Low,
4139  uint64_t High, bool AllowSaturation,
4140  SDValue &Imm) {
4141  if (auto *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N)) {
4142  uint64_t ImmVal = CN->getZExtValue();
4143 
4144  // Reject shift amounts that are too small.
4145  if (ImmVal < Low)
4146  return false;
4147 
4148  // Reject or saturate shift amounts that are too big.
4149  if (ImmVal > High) {
4150  if (!AllowSaturation)
4151  return false;
4152  ImmVal = High;
4153  }
4154 
4155  Imm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmVal, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32);
4156  return true;
4157  }
4158 
4159  return false;
4160 }

4162 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::trySelectStackSlotTagP(SDNode *N) {
4163  // tagp(FrameIndex, IRGstack, tag_offset):
4164  // since the offset between FrameIndex and IRGstack is a compile-time
4165  // constant, this can be lowered to a single ADDG instruction.
4166  if (!(isa<FrameIndexSDNode>(N->getOperand(1)))) {
4167  return false;
4168  }
4169 
4170  SDValue IRG_SP = N->getOperand(2);
4171  if (IRG_SP->getOpcode() != ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN ||
4172  cast<ConstantSDNode>(IRG_SP->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue() !=
4173  Intrinsic::aarch64_irg_sp) {
4174  return false;
4175  }
4176 
4177  const TargetLowering *TLI = getTargetLowering();
4178  SDLoc DL(N);
4179  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getIndex();
4180  SDValue FiOp = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(
4181  FI, TLI->getPointerTy(CurDAG->getDataLayout()));
4182  int TagOffset = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(3))->getZExtValue();
4183 
4184  SDNode *Out = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
4185  AArch64::TAGPstack, DL, MVT::i64,
4186  {FiOp, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i64), N->getOperand(2),
4187  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(TagOffset, DL, MVT::i64)});
4188  ReplaceNode(N, Out);
4189  return true;
4190 }

4192 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectTagP(SDNode *N) {
4193  assert(isa<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(3)) &&
4194  "llvm.aarch64.tagp third argument must be an immediate");
4195  if (trySelectStackSlotTagP(N))
4196  return;
4197  // FIXME: above applies in any case when offset between Op1 and Op2 is a
4198  // compile-time constant, not just for stack allocations.
4199 
4200  // General case for unrelated pointers in Op1 and Op2.
4201  SDLoc DL(N);
4202  int TagOffset = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(3))->getZExtValue();
4203  SDNode *N1 = CurDAG->getMachineNode(AArch64::SUBP, DL, MVT::i64,
4204  {N->getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2)});
4205  SDNode *N2 = CurDAG->getMachineNode(AArch64::ADDXrr, DL, MVT::i64,
4206  {SDValue(N1, 0), N->getOperand(2)});
4207  SDNode *N3 = CurDAG->getMachineNode(
4208  AArch64::ADDG, DL, MVT::i64,
4209  {SDValue(N2, 0), CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i64),
4210  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(TagOffset, DL, MVT::i64)});
4211  ReplaceNode(N, N3);
4212 }
