4214 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::trySelectCastFixedLengthToScalableVector(SDNode *N) {
4215  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR && "Invalid Node!");
4216 
4217  // Bail when not a "cast" like insert_subvector.
4218  if (cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(2))->getZExtValue() != 0)
4219  return false;
4220  if (!N->getOperand(0).isUndef())
4221  return false;
4222 
4223  // Bail when normal isel should do the job.
4224  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4225  EVT InVT = N->getOperand(1).getValueType();
4226  if (VT.isFixedLengthVector() || InVT.isScalableVector())
4227  return false;
4228  if (InVT.getSizeInBits() <= 128)
4229  return false;
4230 
4231  // NOTE: We can only get here when doing fixed length SVE code generation.
4232  // We do manual selection because the types involved are not linked to real
4233  // registers (despite being legal) and must be coerced into SVE registers.
4234 
4235  assert(VT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue() == AArch64::SVEBitsPerBlock &&
4236  "Expected to insert into a packed scalable vector!");
4237 
4238  SDLoc DL(N);
4239  auto RC = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::ZPRRegClassID, DL, MVT::i64);
4240  ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::COPY_TO_REGCLASS, DL, VT,
4241  N->getOperand(1), RC));
4242  return true;
4243 }
4244 
4245 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::trySelectCastScalableToFixedLengthVector(SDNode *N) {
4246  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR && "Invalid Node!");
4247 
4248  // Bail when not a "cast" like extract_subvector.
4249  if (cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue() != 0)
4250  return false;
4251 
4252  // Bail when normal isel can do the job.
4253  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
4254  EVT InVT = N->getOperand(0).getValueType();
4255  if (VT.isScalableVector() || InVT.isFixedLengthVector())
4256  return false;
4257  if (VT.getSizeInBits() <= 128)
4258  return false;
4259 
4260  // NOTE: We can only get here when doing fixed length SVE code generation.
4261  // We do manual selection because the types involved are not linked to real
4262  // registers (despite being legal) and must be coerced into SVE registers.
4263 
4264  assert(InVT.getSizeInBits().getKnownMinValue() == AArch64::SVEBitsPerBlock &&
4265  "Expected to extract from a packed scalable vector!");
4266 
4267  SDLoc DL(N);
4268  auto RC = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(AArch64::ZPRRegClassID, DL, MVT::i64);
4269  ReplaceNode(N, CurDAG->getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::COPY_TO_REGCLASS, DL, VT,
4270  N->getOperand(0), RC));
4271  return true;
4272 }
4273 
4274 void AArch64DAGToDAGISel::Select(SDNode *Node) {
4275  // If we have a custom node, we already have selected!
4276  if (Node->isMachineOpcode()) {
4277  LLVM_DEBUG(errs() << "== "; Node->dump(CurDAG); errs() << "\n");
4278  Node->setNodeId(-1);
4279  return;
4280  }
4281 
4282  // Few custom selection stuff.
4283  EVT VT = Node->getValueType(0);
4284 
4285  switch (Node->getOpcode()) {
4286  default:
4287  break;
4288 
4289  case ISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP:
4290  if (SelectCMP_SWAP(Node))
4291  return;
4292  break;
4293 
4294  case ISD::READ_REGISTER:
4295  case AArch64ISD::MRRS:
4296  if (tryReadRegister(Node))
4297  return;
4298  break;
4299 
4300  case ISD::WRITE_REGISTER:
4301  case AArch64ISD::MSRR:
4302  if (tryWriteRegister(Node))
4303  return;
4304  break;
4305 
4306  case ISD::ADD:
4307  if (tryMLAV64LaneV128(Node))
4308  return;
4309  break;
4310 
4311  case ISD::LOAD: {
4312  // Try to select as an indexed load. Fall through to normal processing
4313  // if we can't.
4314  if (tryIndexedLoad(Node))
4315  return;
4316  break;
4317  }
4318 
4319  case ISD::SRL:
4320  case ISD::AND:
4321  case ISD::SRA:
4322  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
4323  if (tryBitfieldExtractOp(Node))
4324  return;
4325  if (tryBitfieldInsertInZeroOp(Node))
4326  return;
4327  [[fallthrough]];
4328  case ISD::ROTR:
4329  case ISD::SHL:
4330  if (tryShiftAmountMod(Node))
4331  return;
4332  break;
4333 
4334  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
4335  if (tryBitfieldExtractOpFromSExt(Node))
4336  return;
4337  break;
4338 
4339  case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
4340  if (tryHighFPExt(Node))
4341  return;
4342  break;
4343 
4344  case ISD::OR:
4345  if (tryBitfieldInsertOp(Node))
4346  return;
4347  break;
4348 
4349  case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: {
4350  if (trySelectCastScalableToFixedLengthVector(Node))
4351  return;
4352  break;
4353  }
4354 
4355  case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: {
4356  if (trySelectCastFixedLengthToScalableVector(Node))
4357  return;
4358  break;
4359  }
4360 
4361  case ISD::Constant: {
4362  // Materialize zero constants as copies from WZR/XZR. This allows
4363  // the coalescer to propagate these into other instructions.
4364  ConstantSDNode *ConstNode = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Node);
4365  if (ConstNode->isZero()) {
4366  if (VT == MVT::i32) {
4367  SDValue New = CurDAG->getCopyFromReg(
4368  CurDAG->getEntryNode(), SDLoc(Node), AArch64::WZR, MVT::i32);
4369  ReplaceNode(Node, New.getNode());
4370  return;
4371  } else if (VT == MVT::i64) {
4372  SDValue New = CurDAG->getCopyFromReg(
4373  CurDAG->getEntryNode(), SDLoc(Node), AArch64::XZR, MVT::i64);
4374  ReplaceNode(Node, New.getNode());
4375  return;
4376  }
4377  }
4378  break;
4379  }
4380 
4381  case ISD::FrameIndex: {
4382  // Selects to ADDXri FI, 0 which in turn will become ADDXri SP, imm.
4383  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Node)->getIndex();
4384  unsigned Shifter = AArch64_AM::getShifterImm(AArch64_AM::LSL, 0);
4385  const TargetLowering *TLI = getTargetLowering();
4386  SDValue TFI = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(
4387  FI, TLI->getPointerTy(CurDAG->getDataLayout()));
4388  SDLoc DL(Node);
4389  SDValue Ops[] = { TFI, CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32),
4390  CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Shifter, DL, MVT::i32) };
4391  CurDAG->SelectNodeTo(Node, AArch64::ADDXri, MVT::i64, Ops);
4392  return;
4393  }
4394  case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN: {
4395  unsigned IntNo = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Node->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue();
4396  switch (IntNo) {
4397  default:
4398  break;
4399  case Intrinsic::aarch64_ldaxp:
4400  case Intrinsic::aarch64_ldxp: {
4401  unsigned Op =
4402  IntNo == Intrinsic::aarch64_ldaxp ? AArch64::LDAXPX : AArch64::LDXPX;
4403  SDValue MemAddr = Node->getOperand(2);
4404  SDLoc DL(Node);
4405  SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0);
4406 
4407  SDNode *Ld = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Op, DL, MVT::i64, MVT::i64,
4408  MVT::Other, MemAddr, Chain);
4409 
4410  // Transfer memoperands.
4411  MachineMemOperand *MemOp =
4412  cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(Node)->getMemOperand();
4413  CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast<MachineSDNode>(Ld), {MemOp});
4414  ReplaceNode(Node, Ld);
4415  return;
4416  }
4417  case Intrinsic::aarch64_stlxp:
4418  case Intrinsic::aarch64_stxp: {
4419  unsigned Op =
4420  IntNo == Intrinsic::aarch64_stlxp ? AArch64::STLXPX : AArch64::STXPX;
4421  SDLoc DL(Node);
4422  SDValue Chain = Node->getOperand(0);
4423  SDValue ValLo = Node->getOperand(2);
4424  SDValue ValHi = Node->getOperand(3);
4425  SDValue MemAddr = Node->getOperand(4);
4426 
4427  // Place arguments in the right order.
4428  SDValue Ops[] = {ValLo, ValHi, MemAddr, Chain};
4429 
4430  SDNode *St = CurDAG->getMachineNode(Op, DL, MVT::i32, MVT::Other, Ops);
4431  // Transfer memoperands.
4432  MachineMemOperand *MemOp =
4433  cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(Node)->getMemOperand();
4434  CurDAG->setNodeMemRefs(cast<MachineSDNode>(St), {MemOp});
4435 
4436  ReplaceNode(Node, St);
4437  return;
4438  }
4439  case Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld1x2:
4440  if (VT == MVT::v8i8) {
4441  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD1Twov8b, AArch64::dsub0);
4442  return;
4443  } else if (VT == MVT::v16i8) {
4444  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD1Twov16b, AArch64::qsub0);
4445  return;
4446  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i16 || VT == MVT::v4f16 || VT == MVT::v4bf16) {
4447  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD1Twov4h, AArch64::dsub0);
4448  return;
4449  } else if (VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16 || VT == MVT::v8bf16) {
4450  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD1Twov8h, AArch64::qsub0);
4451  return;
4452  } else if (VT == MVT::v2i32 || VT == MVT::v2f32) {
4453  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD1Twov2s, AArch64::dsub0);
4454  return;
4455  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i32 || VT == MVT::v4f32) {
4456  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD1Twov4s, AArch64::qsub0);
4457  return;
4458  } else if (VT == MVT::v1i64 || VT == MVT::v1f64) {
4459  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD1Twov1d, AArch64::dsub0);
4460  return;
4461  } else if (VT == MVT::v2i64 || VT == MVT::v2f64) {
4462  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD1Twov2d, AArch64::qsub0);
4463  return;
4464  }
4465  break;
4466  case Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld1x3:
4467  if (VT == MVT::v8i8) {
4468  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD1Threev8b, AArch64::dsub0);
4469  return;
4470  } else if (VT == MVT::v16i8) {
4471  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD1Threev16b, AArch64::qsub0);
4472  return;
4473  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i16 || VT == MVT::v4f16 || VT == MVT::v4bf16) {
4474  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD1Threev4h, AArch64::dsub0);
4475  return;
4476  } else if (VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16 || VT == MVT::v8bf16) {
4477  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD1Threev8h, AArch64::qsub0);
4478  return;
4479  } else if (VT == MVT::v2i32 || VT == MVT::v2f32) {
4480  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD1Threev2s, AArch64::dsub0);
4481  return;
4482  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i32 || VT == MVT::v4f32) {
4483  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD1Threev4s, AArch64::qsub0);
4484  return;
4485  } else if (VT == MVT::v1i64 || VT == MVT::v1f64) {
4486  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD1Threev1d, AArch64::dsub0);
4487  return;
4488  } else if (VT == MVT::v2i64 || VT == MVT::v2f64) {
4489  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD1Threev2d, AArch64::qsub0);
4490  return;
4491  }
4492  break;
4493  case Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld1x4:
4494  if (VT == MVT::v8i8) {
4495  SelectLoad(Node, 4, AArch64::LD1Fourv8b, AArch64::dsub0);
4496  return;
4497  } else if (VT == MVT::v16i8) {
4498  SelectLoad(Node, 4, AArch64::LD1Fourv16b, AArch64::qsub0);
4499  return;
4500  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i16 || VT == MVT::v4f16 || VT == MVT::v4bf16) {
4501  SelectLoad(Node, 4, AArch64::LD1Fourv4h, AArch64::dsub0);
4502  return;
4503  } else if (VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16 || VT == MVT::v8bf16) {
4504  SelectLoad(Node, 4, AArch64::LD1Fourv8h, AArch64::qsub0);
4505  return;
4506  } else if (VT == MVT::v2i32 || VT == MVT::v2f32) {
4507  SelectLoad(Node, 4, AArch64::LD1Fourv2s, AArch64::dsub0);
4508  return;
4509  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i32 || VT == MVT::v4f32) {
4510  SelectLoad(Node, 4, AArch64::LD1Fourv4s, AArch64::qsub0);
4511  return;
4512  } else if (VT == MVT::v1i64 || VT == MVT::v1f64) {
4513  SelectLoad(Node, 4, AArch64::LD1Fourv1d, AArch64::dsub0);
4514  return;
4515  } else if (VT == MVT::v2i64 || VT == MVT::v2f64) {
4516  SelectLoad(Node, 4, AArch64::LD1Fourv2d, AArch64::qsub0);
4517  return;
4518  }
4519  break;
4520  case Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld2:
4521  if (VT == MVT::v8i8) {
4522  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD2Twov8b, AArch64::dsub0);
4523  return;
4524  } else if (VT == MVT::v16i8) {
4525  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD2Twov16b, AArch64::qsub0);
4526  return;
4527  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i16 || VT == MVT::v4f16 || VT == MVT::v4bf16) {
4528  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD2Twov4h, AArch64::dsub0);
4529  return;
4530  } else if (VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16 || VT == MVT::v8bf16) {

4541  return;
4542  } else if (VT == MVT::v2i64 || VT == MVT::v2f64) {
4543  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD2Twov2d, AArch64::qsub0);
4544  return;
4545  }
4546  break;
4547  case Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld3:
4548  if (VT == MVT::v8i8) {
4549  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD3Threev8b, AArch64::dsub0);
4550  return;
4551  } else if (VT == MVT::v16i8) {
4552  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD3Threev16b, AArch64::qsub0);
4553  return;
4554  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i16 || VT == MVT::v4f16 || VT == MVT::v4bf16) {
4555  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD3Threev4h, AArch64::dsub0);
4556  return;
4557  } else if (VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16 || VT == MVT::v8bf16) {
4558  SelectLoad(Node, 3, AArch64::LD3Threev8h, AArch64::qsub0);
4559  return;
4560  } else if (VT == MVT::v2i32 || VT == MVT::v2f32) {

4563  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i32 || VT == MVT::v4f32) {

4577  return;
4578  } else if (VT == MVT::v16i8) {

4584  } else if (VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16 || VT == MVT::v8bf16) {

4586  return;
4587  } else if (VT == MVT::v2i32 || VT == MVT::v2f32) {

4594  SelectLoad(Node, 4, AArch64::LD1Fourv1d, AArch64::dsub0);

4600  break;
4601  case Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld2r:
4602  if (VT == MVT::v8i8) {
4603  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD2Rv8b, AArch64::dsub0);
4604  return;
4605  } else if (VT == MVT::v16i8) {
4606  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD2Rv16b, AArch64::qsub0);
4607  return;
4608  } else if (VT == MVT::v4i16 || VT == MVT::v4f16 || VT == MVT::v4bf16) {
4609  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD2Rv4h, AArch64::dsub0);
4610  return;
4611  } else if (VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16 || VT == MVT::v8bf16) {
4612  SelectLoad(Node, 2, AArch64::LD2Rv8h, AArch64::qsub0);

4700  case Intrinsic::aarch64_neon_ld3lane:
4701  if (VT == MVT::v16i8 || VT == MVT::v8i8) {
4702  SelectLoadLane(Node, 3, AArch64::LD3i8);
4703  return;

6322  }
6323  case AArch64ISD::SVE_LD3_MERGE_ZERO: {
6324  if (VT == MVT::nxv16i8) {
6325  SelectPredicatedLoad(Node, 3, 0, AArch64::LD3B_IMM, AArch64::LD3B);
6326  return;
6327  } else if (VT == MVT::nxv8i16 || VT == MVT::nxv8f16 ||
6328  VT == MVT::nxv8bf16) {
6329  SelectPredicatedLoad(Node, 3, 1, AArch64::LD3H_IMM, AArch64::LD3H);
6330  return;
6331  } else if (VT == MVT::nxv4i32 || VT == MVT::nxv4f32) {
6332  SelectPredicatedLoad(Node, 3, 2, AArch64::LD3W_IMM, AArch64::LD3W);
6333  return;
6334  } else if (VT == MVT::nxv2i64 || VT == MVT::nxv2f64) {
6335  SelectPredicatedLoad(Node, 3, 3, AArch64::LD3D_IMM, AArch64::LD3D);
6336  return;
6337  }
6338  break;
6339  }
6340  case AArch64ISD::SVE_LD4_MERGE_ZERO: {
6341  if (VT == MVT::nxv16i8) {
6342  SelectPredicatedLoad(Node, 4, 0, AArch64::LD4B_IMM, AArch64::LD4B);
6343  return;
6344  } else if (VT == MVT::nxv8i16 || VT == MVT::nxv8f16 ||
6345  VT == MVT::nxv8bf16) {
6346  SelectPredicatedLoad(Node, 4, 1, AArch64::LD4H_IMM, AArch64::LD4H);
6347  return;
6348  } else if (VT == MVT::nxv4i32 || VT == MVT::nxv4f32) {
6349  SelectPredicatedLoad(Node, 4, 2, AArch64::LD4W_IMM, AArch64::LD4W);
6350  return;
6351  } else if (VT == MVT::nxv2i64 || VT == MVT::nxv2f64) {
6352  SelectPredicatedLoad(Node, 4, 3, AArch64::LD4D_IMM, AArch64::LD4D);
6353  return;
6354  }
6355  break;
6356  }
6357  }
6358 
6359  // Select the default instruction
6360  SelectCode(Node);
6361 }
6362 
6363 /// createAArch64ISelDag - This pass converts a legalized DAG into a
6364 /// AArch64-specific DAG, ready for instruction scheduling.
6365 FunctionPass *llvm::createAArch64ISelDag(AArch64TargetMachine &TM,
6366  CodeGenOpt::Level OptLevel) {
6367  return new AArch64DAGToDAGISel(TM, OptLevel);
6368 }

6370 /// When \p PredVT is a scalable vector predicate in the form
6371 /// MVT::nx<M>xi1, it builds the correspondent scalable vector of
6372 /// integers MVT::nx<M>xi<bits> s.t. M x bits = 128. When targeting
6373 /// structured vectors (NumVec >1), the output data type is
6374 /// MVT::nx<M*NumVec>xi<bits> s.t. M x bits = 128. If the input
6375 /// PredVT is not in the form MVT::nx<M>xi1, it returns an invalid
6376 /// EVT.
6377 static EVT getPackedVectorTypeFromPredicateType(LLVMContext &Ctx, EVT PredVT,
6378  unsigned NumVec) {
6379  assert(NumVec > 0 && NumVec < 5 && "Invalid number of vectors.");
6380  if (!PredVT.isScalableVector() || PredVT.getVectorElementType() != MVT::i1)
6381  return EVT();
6382 
6383  if (PredVT != MVT::nxv16i1 && PredVT != MVT::nxv8i1 &&
6384  PredVT != MVT::nxv4i1 && PredVT != MVT::nxv2i1)
6385  return EVT();
6386 
6387  ElementCount EC = PredVT.getVectorElementCount();
6388  EVT ScalarVT =
6389  EVT::getIntegerVT(Ctx, AArch64::SVEBitsPerBlock / EC.getKnownMinValue());
6390  EVT MemVT = EVT::getVectorVT(Ctx, ScalarVT, EC * NumVec);
6391 
6392  return MemVT;
6393 }
6394 
6395 /// Return the EVT of the data associated to a memory operation in \p
6396 /// Root. If such EVT cannot be retrived, it returns an invalid EVT.
6397 static EVT getMemVTFromNode(LLVMContext &Ctx, SDNode *Root) {
6398  if (isa<MemSDNode>(Root))
6399  return cast<MemSDNode>(Root)->getMemoryVT();
6400 
6401  if (isa<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(Root))
6402  return cast<MemIntrinsicSDNode>(Root)->getMemoryVT();
6403 
6404  const unsigned Opcode = Root->getOpcode();
6405  // For custom ISD nodes, we have to look at them individually to extract the
6406  // type of the data moved to/from memory.
6407  switch (Opcode) {
6408  case AArch64ISD::LD1_MERGE_ZERO:
6409  case AArch64ISD::LD1S_MERGE_ZERO:
6410  case AArch64ISD::LDNF1_MERGE_ZERO:
6411  case AArch64ISD::LDNF1S_MERGE_ZERO:
6412  return cast<VTSDNode>(Root->getOperand(3))->getVT();
6413  case AArch64ISD::ST1_PRED:
6414  return cast<VTSDNode>(Root->getOperand(4))->getVT();
6415  case AArch64ISD::SVE_LD2_MERGE_ZERO:
6416  return getPackedVectorTypeFromPredicateType(
6417  Ctx, Root->getOperand(1)->getValueType(0), /*NumVec=*/2);
6418  case AArch64ISD::SVE_LD3_MERGE_ZERO:
6419  return getPackedVectorTypeFromPredicateType(
6420  Ctx, Root->getOperand(1)->getValueType(0), /*NumVec=*/3);
6421  case AArch64ISD::SVE_LD4_MERGE_ZERO:
6422  return getPackedVectorTypeFromPredicateType(
6423  Ctx, Root->getOperand(1)->getValueType(0), /*NumVec=*/4);
6424  default:
6425  break;
6426  }
6427 
6428  if (Opcode != ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID && Opcode != ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN)
6429  return EVT();
6430 
6431  switch (cast<ConstantSDNode>(Root->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue()) {
6432  default:
6433  return EVT();
6434  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sme_ldr:
6435  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sme_str:
6436  return MVT::nxv16i8;
6437  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_prf:
6438  // We are using an SVE prefetch intrinsic. Type must be inferred from the
6439  // width of the predicate.
6440  return getPackedVectorTypeFromPredicateType(
6441  Ctx, Root->getOperand(2)->getValueType(0), /*NumVec=*/1);
6442  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_ld2_sret:
6443  return getPackedVectorTypeFromPredicateType(
6444  Ctx, Root->getOperand(2)->getValueType(0), /*NumVec=*/2);
6445  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_ld3_sret:
6446  return getPackedVectorTypeFromPredicateType(
6447  Ctx, Root->getOperand(2)->getValueType(0), /*NumVec=*/3);
6448  case Intrinsic::aarch64_sve_ld4_sret:
6449  return getPackedVectorTypeFromPredicateType(
6450  Ctx, Root->getOperand(2)->getValueType(0), /*NumVec=*/4);
6451  }
6452 }
6453 
6454 /// SelectAddrModeIndexedSVE - Attempt selection of the addressing mode:
6455 /// Base + OffImm * sizeof(MemVT) for Min >= OffImm <= Max
6456 /// where Root is the memory access using N for its address.
6457 template <int64_t Min, int64_t Max>
6458 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectAddrModeIndexedSVE(SDNode *Root, SDValue N,
6459  SDValue &Base,
6460  SDValue &OffImm) {
6461  const EVT MemVT = getMemVTFromNode(*(CurDAG->getContext()), Root);
6462  const DataLayout &DL = CurDAG->getDataLayout();
6463  const MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF->getFrameInfo();
6464 
6465  if (N.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) {
6466  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(N)->getIndex();
6467  // We can only encode VL scaled offsets, so only fold in frame indexes
6468  // referencing SVE objects.
6469  if (FI == 0 || MFI.getStackID(FI) == TargetStackID::ScalableVector) {
6470  Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI, TLI->getPointerTy(DL));
6471  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(N), MVT::i64);
6472  return true;
6473  }
6474 
6475  return false;
6476  }
6477 
6478  if (MemVT == EVT())
6479  return false;
6480 
6481  if (N.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD)
6482  return false;
6483 
6484  SDValue VScale = N.getOperand(1);
6485  if (VScale.getOpcode() != ISD::VSCALE)
6486  return false;
6487 
6488  TypeSize TS = MemVT.getSizeInBits();
6489  int64_t MemWidthBytes = static_cast<int64_t>(TS.getKnownMinValue()) / 8;
6490  int64_t MulImm = cast<ConstantSDNode>(VScale.getOperand(0))->getSExtValue();
6491 
6492  if ((MulImm % MemWidthBytes) != 0)
6493  return false;
6494 
6495  int64_t Offset = MulImm / MemWidthBytes;
6496  if (Offset < Min || Offset > Max)
6497  return false;
6498 
6499  Base = N.getOperand(0);
6500  if (Base.getOpcode() == ISD::FrameIndex) {
6501  int FI = cast<FrameIndexSDNode>(Base)->getIndex();
6502  // We can only encode VL scaled offsets, so only fold in frame indexes
6503  // referencing SVE objects.
6504  if (FI == 0 || MFI.getStackID(FI) == TargetStackID::ScalableVector)
6505  Base = CurDAG->getTargetFrameIndex(FI, TLI->getPointerTy(DL));
6506  }
6507 
6508  OffImm = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(Offset, SDLoc(N), MVT::i64);
6509  return true;
6510 }
6511 
6512 /// Select register plus register addressing mode for SVE, with scaled
6513 /// offset.
6514 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectSVERegRegAddrMode(SDValue N, unsigned Scale,
6515  SDValue &Base,
6516  SDValue &Offset) {
6517  if (N.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD)
6518  return false;
6519 
6520  // Process an ADD node.
6521  const SDValue LHS = N.getOperand(0);
6522  const SDValue RHS = N.getOperand(1);
6523 
6524  // 8 bit data does not come with the SHL node, so it is treated
6525  // separately.
6526  if (Scale == 0) {
6527  Base = LHS;
6528  Offset = RHS;
6529  return true;
6530  }
6531 
6532  if (auto C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS)) {
6533  int64_t ImmOff = C->getSExtValue();
6534  unsigned Size = 1 << Scale;
6535 
6536  // To use the reg+reg addressing mode, the immediate must be a multiple of
6537  // the vector element's byte size.
6538  if (ImmOff % Size)
6539  return false;
6540 
6541  SDLoc DL(N);
6542  Base = LHS;
6543  Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmOff >> Scale, DL, MVT::i64);
6544  SDValue Ops[] = {Offset};
6545  SDNode *MI = CurDAG->getMachineNode(AArch64::MOVi64imm, DL, MVT::i64, Ops);
6546  Offset = SDValue(MI, 0);
6547  return true;
6548  }
6549 
6550  // Check if the RHS is a shift node with a constant.
6551  if (RHS.getOpcode() != ISD::SHL)
6552  return false;
6553 
6554  const SDValue ShiftRHS = RHS.getOperand(1);
6555  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(ShiftRHS))
6556  if (C->getZExtValue() == Scale) {
6557  Base = LHS;
6558  Offset = RHS.getOperand(0);
6559  return true;
6560  }
6561 
6562  return false;
6563 }
6564 
6565 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectAllActivePredicate(SDValue N) {
6566  const AArch64TargetLowering *TLI =
6567  static_cast<const AArch64TargetLowering *>(getTargetLowering());
6568 
6569  return TLI->isAllActivePredicate(*CurDAG, N);
6570 }
6571 
6572 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectAnyPredicate(SDValue N) {
6573  EVT VT = N.getValueType();
6574  return VT.isScalableVector() && VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1;
6575 }

6577 bool AArch64DAGToDAGISel::SelectSMETileSlice(SDValue N, unsigned MaxSize,
6578  SDValue &Base, SDValue &Offset,
6579  unsigned Scale) {
6580  if (N.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD) {
6581  Base = N;
6582  Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(0, SDLoc(N), MVT::i64);
6583  return true;
6584  }
6585 
6586  // Process an ADD node.
6587  const SDValue LHS = N.getOperand(0);
6588  const SDValue RHS = N.getOperand(1);
6589 
6590  if (auto C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS)) {
6591  int64_t ImmOff = C->getSExtValue();
6592 
6593  if ((ImmOff < 0 || ImmOff > MaxSize) || (ImmOff % Scale != 0))
6594  return false;
6595 
6596  Base = LHS;
6597  Offset = CurDAG->getTargetConstant(ImmOff / Scale, SDLoc(N), MVT::i64);
6598  return true;
6599  }
6600 
6601  return false;
6602 }
